text:
dear america,
i never agreed to be black. or what you’ve agreed that it is before me. we are told who we are by societies’ agreements. but my ancestors had no seat at the table, no consent in something that concerned them and their descendants. dealing with the results of agreements we made for ourselves is fair. if you agree to be a doctor, a dj, to a marriage or a friendship — there are aspects of life that are obtainable and certain ones that are not based on your agreements. this is natural. don’t like aspects of your life? you’re free to change agreements around your job or break off relationships. 
what isn’t natural; we demand and expect full participation in the predetermined agreements around race without the consent of the people who are affected by them the most. kinda like a #metoo on life itself. life abuse. demanding my participation in this abuse america and its institutions have perpetrated against those of my shade with impunity is the antithesis of liberty. my liberty as a citizen and the liberty of my soul as a conscious being. my acceptance of the agreement is my imprisonment. even the soft bigotry of low expectations is a burden too heavy for my unwilling shoulders. some of you may be amused, others confused, some angered by the sheer notion of what i’m suggesting. black and white alike. understand that i don’t care enough about white privilege to appease it and i don’t care enough about black burden to continue to carry it or fulfill someone else’s expectations surrounding it. being black should not mean being burdened by a nation or a mind. i didn’t agree to participate in this charade of value. race is an invention. unlike others it has yet to prove its usefulness. but has a purpose for the inventor. it‘s been a weapon to divide would be allies in the truth of human equity. separating us from our common struggles and imprisons our ideas and thoughts about ourselves and others. which allows the status quo to remain. that’s only good for who’s currently in power. i won’t allow my true self to be imprisoned. not by a society or my own mind. self that is beyond race and gender. what we call a soul. i’m writing a book on this. more to come. ᐂ

text:
do you want to know a secret. . . ? 
you are beautiful as you are, right here, right now.  your body is beautiful as it is, right here, right now.

why am i sharing this “secret” with you?  well, i have seen many, many, many women struggle the night of and day after the victoria’s secret fashion show - which was on tonight.

before you begin to compare yourself to those beautiful ladies that were strutting down the walkway on your big screen tv, take a pause.  remember that they are a very small minority of what women look like.  majority of the women in this world do not look like that - and that is okay. .

you have your own attributes that make you your special and unique self.  playing the comparison game will only make you feel like shit - and that’s not a good way to end the weekend or begin a new week.

you are beautiful - just as you are - right here, right now.

you are beautiful 💜

you have your own attributes that make you your special and unique self.  playing the comparison game will only make you feel like shit - and that’s not a good way to end the weekend or begin a new week.

you are beautiful - just as you are - right here, right now.

you are beautiful 💜

text: trigger warning! details on why i didn't report (my rape) when i was homeless. i was out of the loop and laying low when the #whyididntreport hashtag gained momentum. but it's good that it did and even though i have not wanted to participate in #metoo discussions, i feel i'm at a place now where i can. at least for now. i posted a 10 min video to my mermeia channel which you can access in my bio. if you can stomach the topic and want to check it out, please do. it is a super complicated subject. perpetrators of assault and harrassment do not discriminate against age, gender, or a person's integrity or self worth. it can happen to anyone. and the reasons why people don't report are as different as each individual survivor. #believesurvivors #believewomen #believemen #hurtpeoplehurtpeople #metoo #sexualassault #sexualabuse #sexualharassment #endthecycle #ptsd #ptsdrecovery #survivor @whyididntreport @ronanfarrow

text:
i posted this on fb, posting here too. update on my absence and a look into my heart. hoping to educate and minister. warning, it is a heart full.

my voice has been silenced, ignored, manipulated, rejected, used, abused, bullied, and discarded.
i'm taking a stand to say: enough is enough.

the time has come for me to speak on here. 
it’s not for validation, consolation, forgiveness, approval or revenge, but for the sake of truth. 
please know and hear that i am speaking from a place of being humbled greatly and continuing to be, from being blinded by sin, and from a place of deep, agonizing pain. pain from which has hit me in waves and the waves keep coming. 
it started out with grief in the loss of a person i truly, deeply loved with great strength and heart. all memories, experiences were curated deep. the good and the bad. why? because i loved and i tried to surrender each moment to god, walk as he would have me. to which i failed again and again and again, but i chose to keep walking. it was my joy to walk with him. my saying yes to him the second time (yes second time)  was not taken lightly, it was not nothing. (and t, no, it was not because i was not dating anyone else. how dare you talk as if you know my story.  oh the terrible counsel to which he was given to come to me, just because he desired… more on that later). i had not talked to him for years. enough time for us to grow and mature. he reached out to me so unexpectedly. i was curious though my heart still very cold towards him. we meet up and unexpectedly, my heart thawed. i saw him and remembered all the things, the reasons why i was with him long ago. he felt like home, i thought he was safe. if you knew our story, years ago we dated and were engaged. this wasn’t a person i was going to mess around with. i was going to be honest and put it all the table. and so i did. i’m in it for the long haul. and this wasn’t flippant for me. i reached out to mentors, my family, friends, prayed, and processed together. 
the truth is that he was never safe and still is not safe. he never loved me and is very twisted on what love and care is. he just used and abused me. eight plus years of it. (cont. ⬇️)
name: CHELSEY LYNEA

a nightwood theatre production in association with crow’s theatre | written by jane doe* | directed by andrea donaldson 
featuring michaela washburn, rose napoli, brenda robins and conrad coates .

tickets available at crowstheatre.com.

photography by @tanjatiziana .

text:
this is me now. 
however dec 3, 2017 was a day i thought i would never live to see.  i made a choice to not only keep my kids safe, but myself. enough was enough. i was granted a gift.
i knew i had so much more life to live. i had to be strong.
i wanted to set an example for my daughter. for all women.
for anyone who didn't believe they were worth more or deserved more.
 i was scared, but i was strong. i was nervous, but i was fierce. i chose me. 
i still check over my shoulder. sometimes i feel uneasy. but i will not hide in fear. i will not allow someone to have control over my life ever again.

#metoo #instawomen #domesticviolence #speakup #healing #onedayatatime #actnow #help #awareness

text: the healing process was and still is difficult...the nightmares, the flash backs, the anxiety while in the car or alone with somebody...it takes time y’all! it’s so important to seek support. in my case i found a therapist i was comfortable with and was able to process it with. not only that i began working with victims and was able to educate students from elementary school up to college on sexual assault awareness. i found it in myself to help others who could be or have been in my situation or similar. i continue to work on me, help others, identify my triggers, and to find forgiveness in my heart and forgive those who have hurt me and others sexually, mentally, and physically. i have become so much stronger and although if i could i would absolutely take back that night and the terror i felt...i am thankful for my life at where i am now...i am thankful for the strong woman i have become, and the things i have learned. this tattoo represents more than just the sexual assault ribbon...it means a lot to me...”we all carry these things inside that no one else can see. they hold us down like anchors, they drown us out at sea...but i refuse to sink. life's roughest storms prove the strengths of our anchors.” ❤️

text:
‪"winter is here, blame persephone!" i used to say. recently i noticed it was not her fault.‬
-
‪persephone was the beautiful daughter of demeter, the goddess of harvest and fertility, and zeus the king of gods of mount olympus. basically, upsetting persephone's parents was a really bad idea but hades, god of the underworld, never got the memo. he fell "in love" with the sheltered persephone.‬
-
‪in greek mythology, hades is described as a middle aged man, living in the shadows with the dead.  demeter furiously rejects hades's proposal to marry persephone. so the "heartbroken" god of underworld kidnaps persephone. he takes her to the underworld...into the darkness.‬
-
‪poor persephone cries day and night. versions of the tale say persephone stopped eating, only cried, and hades rapes her. ‬
-
‪above ground, her mother demeter searched for persephone everywhere. she too cries night and day but her sadness has severe immediate implications to her surroundings.‬
-
‪as the god of harvest and fertility, demeter's sadness affected the world. plants started to die, leaves started to dry and it became cold.‬
-
‪some versions of the tale say that eating anything in the underworld meant you had to stay there. persephone eats only one thing. tempted by the ruby color and nagging hunger, she eats only 6 grains of a pomegranate. only six.‬
-
her mother locates her and zeus summons them to mount olympus. hades makes the case that persephone ate in the underground...and belongs to him.‬ ‪
-
they come to an agreement. for 6 months out of the year, persephone would be with her mother. during those months, demeter would be happy and the earth would have spring and summer. but the last 6 months, in the absence of persephone, it would be autumn and winter.‬ ‪
-
this myth was created to explain the changing of seasons. i remember my middle school class concluded that winter is persephone's fault. she ate from the forbidden pomegranate after all.‬ ‪
-
but no. winter is here, blame hades. ‬ ‪
-
and thank god those pomegranates weren't from kandahar or else..we would have winter all year.‬ ‪
-
second picture is the sculpture from 1622 by ‬bernini‪ called the rape of persephone.

text:
💕💕💕
👏👏👏 .
.
@thesarahdoughty
・・・
sometimes women learn the hard way of what it means to freeze in the face of danger. it's a learned habit, sometimes even when no danger is present. body language can speak a thousand words. there is a difference between consent and vacancy. never assume her silence is consent.
— b o d y  l a n g u a g e
© sarah doughty
.
think about this. if she's making eyes, it doesn't mean consent. if she's barely dressed, it doesn't mean consent. did it ever occur to you that asking if it's okay is not only sexy, but empowering? if she doesn't say yes, the answer is no.
.
.
you might be wondering why i'm sharing this now. you may wonder why anyone with a story of abuse or assault may wait decades before coming forward — if they ever say anything at all. the answer is simple: any time is a good time. the issue is unfortunate. that there's not enough people talking about this and how important it is to not only know the difference, but to stop blaming the victims. start conversations. teach your children what's okay and what is not. just do something.
.
and right now, that's exactly what i'm doing. 'we will not be silenced' is an important anthology of poetry, prose, essays, and even art for everyone — survivors, victims, help centers, and even law enforcement. and yes, you. find more information about this book and what you can do to help on my website.
.
#metoo
.
if you want to learn more about my free books and where to get them, head to the link in my bio and click on book links.
.
illustration by the incredible @drasan_art.
.
#sarahdoughty ✧ @thesarahdoughty

if i don’t mix up my workouts- i get bored- when i get bored i get burnt out- and burn out leads to me not being happy. so tonight i mixed up different types of cardio and different lifts. of course my favorite part was the run. video clip was taken at a 6:58 pace 🔥 which left strong and lovely. i surprise myself sometimes. i don’t know where my journey is headed. none of us do. just keep moving forward and enjoy the scenery with a few close friends that want to travel with you ❤️ hows that? are you enlightened? i sure hope so 🙏❤️ #oymambassador #hairstylist  #inkedgirl #explantista #marathoner #procompressionambassador #runnersrepost  #poweryourpassion  #noexcuses #runspiration #strength #runnerscommunity #motherrunner #getafterit #girlswholift

text:
💯 truth💣 from my good friend, tcm school twinsie🕺💃, and amazing acupuncturist @acupunctureriley (follow him😉)
💫💫
if there is one message my practice (my own life and yoga practice  and working with others in a clinical or studio setting) reflects, it is this!!!! 💫💫
over the past 17 years i have done, lived by, and tried almost every detox, cleanse, diet out there.  what i discovered, what i digest (notice i didn't write "eat") matters a lot but what brings about the big, transformational, life changing shifts is when the stuff of the 💓 (emotions) and mind are addressed...not ignored or stuffed, but brought to the surface, acknowledged, hugged, and then released. 💫💫
chinese medicine and ayurveda, both complete forms of medicine (continuously practiced since before jesus was born), have specific practices (points on the body, mantras, songs, meditations, physical practices, foods, gems, the list goes on and on) for treatment modalities to address the harmony of the mind and emotions. 💫💫
i am still finding corners of my body, heart, and mind where the emotional and mental stuff (beliefs, fears, etc) that comes with sexual trauma hide.  there are so many useful ways to heal from sexual trauma but for me the most profound healing, lasting healing, and empowering healing has come from asian medicines (yoga, acupuncture, and ayurveda). that's also why i am soooooooo passionate about sharing the heart of these medicines with you 😁😘😊 if you've read this far, thank you.  i'm still open to a few more motivated people to join my beta online workshops in ayurveda and chinese medicine.  pm or comment below if you want me to add you. 🙏✨✨✨ #healingcomesfromwithin #yogalife #yogaoffthemat
#yogaheals #chinesemedicine #chinesemedicineheals  #ayurveda #ayurvedaheals #acupuncture #youaredivine #holisticminded #yogamom #yogateacherinspiration #bethechange #theworldneedsyourlight #metoo

text:
have you ever practiced lucid dreaming? some have the ability to control and manipulate what happens in their dreams. if you’re interested in giving it a go, perhaps start by setting yourself up with a sleep meditation from youtube - i recommend 432 hz frequency audios. try to remember what happens in the dream, or start the dream out by visualizing the same thing days in a row. push the limitations of your mind, open up and fly. often lucid dreamers will keep a diary and write down what they’ve seen and experienced. don’t be afraid to reference books or articles for certain meanings. did you know that as a woman, if you dream of a cow, you are pregnant? just food for thought on the warm sunday night. sweet dreams ✨

text: ** there is nothing funny about domestic violence ** everything this $13 billion brand has done since midweek has shown me that it couldn't care less about getting a grip on domestic violence in text:
scary thing # 2✌🏻
brought woolvas to a market. 《》i had been watching the #metoo movement build with wide eyes. i was so proud of these people, and so sad for them too. so many women affected by revolting behaviour that had been tolerated, and accepted by society at large. i wasn’t in denial about my own experiences - many of which are really scary, and we’ll get to them in another post, another time, but i didn’t feel that i had the right to see those assaults as part of metoo. obviously part of my grooming to accept assault and harassment as life as usual. 《》
bullshit. such absolute bullshit. 
i had never felt that my body was my own. 
sex, although fun with my current partner, still held issues for me. 
because of what men had done to me without my consent. 
because of the humans around me who normalized abuse. 
because of the shame cast upon survivors of rape. 💪🏻
💪🏻
a woolva is fibre art piece made to resemble a vulva. 
woolvas are the reclaiming of vulvas as our own. 
my vulva is beautiful, and unique, and i deserve to love it, as does every woman. vulvas aren’t vulgar. 《》
i love making woolvas, and i love what they stand for. 
i wanted to shared them - but would people connect?
《》
enter freewheeling - in february 2018 there was a valentine’s market. my weekdays are saturdays and sundays, and i didn’t feel confident that i could justify taking time off work for a gamble - like art. but as luck would have it, there was a friday night i could sell at - amanda at freewheeling gave me the a-ok to set up. 
i’m glad she gave me the shot, cause geezus i love it! although, i embarrassingly had to ask a neighbour how to use my square app for my first sale. like a friggin’ geriatric, i couldn’t figure out to just touch the button. 👵🏻🤦🏼‍
my goal was just to experience it, and to break even. pretty lofty, i know. well holy schmoly - i hit my goal plus a little extra | i almost didn’t apply to be a vendor - i wasn’t sure anyone would connect to my feminist art. they did connect with it though, and it may have actually been the reason for all the changes that followed through the year. 《》
i'll take weekends off in 2019 to be at more freewheeling events.

text:
i was 16 the first time a man ever put his hands on me. he said he loved me and with a shift in the atmosphere came the palms of his hands to my face. he called me all out my name and told me no man one would ever want me but him. the crazy part is, at 16, i believed him.

at 18 i met another man. he loved me too. he loved me so much that he wrapped his right hand around my neck, squeezing every airway shut. with his right hand planted, his left hand grabbed a water bottle and he dashed water in my face so that with every gasp of air i even attempted to take, water would fill my lungs making it impossible to breathe.

glad to see 21, i met someone new. he was different. he was the first man to ever take me to church. he loved me so much that he told me he wanted me to bare his child. he sold me every dream and i bought all of them. until at 7 months pregnant he pushed me out of car. until i was laying in a hospital bed about to give birth to the only life i had left inside of me and i was hiding bruises and bite marks under my gown.

so many of you ask me, “how did @turningpaiges_ begin?” it began when god gave me the courage to not give up on life but to instead start turning the pages in my own life to get to new chapters. better chapters. so why do i love so hard? because i know what it’s like to feel loveless. why do i speak out against injustices? because i know what it’s like to wish that someone would have noticed and spoke up about the injustices done to me. why do i serve? because that’s how i love god, and love heals. i’m @turningpaiges_ because turning pages in the book of life, being the bible, taught me truth and god made all things brand new for me. why wouldn’t i share that?

text:
made this peice at 4:30 am, after spending time thinking too much, worrying too much. i was thinking about home the whole time, and i couldn't help but make something that i hope to see this winter. i've never been sking and i really haven't felt free in a while until i imagined it. as my brush stroked the canvas in shades of blue and white, i felt myself glide and roll in the snow, cold air brushing my cheeks. i lived it.
i stopped painting when my depression got worse. i couldn't express myself anymore, i couldn't do the things i used to enjoy, i couldn't love the same. i wasn't someone i, or anyone recognised. i don't know why i picked the paint brush again, perhaps nothing was entertaining me anymore, or maybe, just maybe...a new beginning

text: “when i was young i experienced my first sexual assault. it continued, through adolescence and in different circumstances i’d learned to just endure it. it evolved into accepting abusive relationships in my adult life. one day i woke up and had enough of the abuse. i changed my life and began to seek help. through my wellness, i’ve been diagnosed with ptsd, depression and anxiety, due to the many sexual assaults and abuse i’ve endured. i feel that awareness is important because there are many different levels of trauma, and everyone’s case is so vastly different. any person can make a huge impact on another knowingly or even unknowingly, so it’s important to always be kind, and respectful. this necklace signifies the pain i’ve experienced and strength i’ve gained through it to overcome and help anyone who may need it.” @ganjanelly 💙 #awarecauses

text:
i recently read an article in which the author posited that in order to be successful, it was better to cultivate a variety of skills that complement each other than it was to master a single skill. he was talking about skills in the workplace, but i believe this line of thinking can be applied to any area of our lives. in this case, i apply it to my active endeavors. i thought i had the perfect combination with my trail running + rock climbing. they are perfect complements to each other for my mountain adventures. so where does martial arts fit into that?
.
this month, i celebrate a year of martial arts, a sport i got into almost accidentally and somewhat reluctantly. while i have enjoyed it, it wasn’t until this past month or so when i made the commitment to getting my black belt and started participating in the extra leadership classes that i have started to love this sport too.
.
the thing that i love about kyuki-do is that it combines the kicks and punches of one discipline with the self-defense and weapons training of others. i started leadership classes on a month where the focus was on grappling and we spent entire sessions throwing each other. but when my 5’1”, 111 lb self tossed a fully grown, larger-than-average man over my shoulder, it came to me as i heard the thud of his body hitting the mats when he landed at my feet. i remember looking at my small hands afterwards thinking, “i did that.”
.
a day or two earlier, i had read a horrifying account of an elite hungarian ultra runner who had been brutally attacked and sexually assaulted while out on a run. like her, the reality is that i mostly train, travel, and adventure on my own and i have to worry about this happening to me too. but where i’ve been conditioned to be polite and subservient and not cause a scene, here i am taught to yell, say no, be intense, defend and hit back because my safety is more important than someone’s feelings. in a world where evil will always exist, rhetoric won’t save me. all of my precautions might not be enough. but like @run_kiwi_run, i now have a much better chance at saying, “not today, motherfucker” and living to run another day.

text:
counting down the last two weeks left of undergrad life. & yes, i am flicking off my cap because the struggles it took to get this far is what led me into my field. this is my mini story of how the health care field chose me and to say that we are not alone in adversity:
i am a first-generation college student from a socioeconomically depressed community. coming from a disadvantaged background, the social barriers and determinants that stood in my way stripped away my childhood and young adulthood because my existence was surrounded by substance, physical and sexual abuse. while my original coping mechanism was to hide them away tucked in the back of my mind, i have come to realize that i did not withstand these experiences for nothing. i was meant to use these experiences as the foundation to understand and help others survive together through our shared experiences. although i have been stripped apart of who i was, i am defining who i am in spite of the tremendous amount of adversity i’ve endured. i like the term endurance to describe the long nights i lay awake in bed crying myself to sleep at night, not being able to look at myself in the mirror, feelings of loneliness and complete inconsolable grief to recognize that through the blurred lenses, i am a survivor. to get through my 5 years of schooling is only a tidbit of the challenges that stood in my way, but i found myself here in public health because i vowed for no little girl to ever have to endure the same hardships that i’ve had too if i can prevent it. however, my kuleana is too all the people of hawai’i, it just started from being the broken little girl myself. and for those who wear their broken hearts on their sleeves, the scars on their arms, the tears in their eyes, the pain hidden behind a smile or a laugh just know i am with you on this journey and we are all survivors. the next steps now in my career is to embrace adversity, look it in the eyes and give voice to survivors because we are a resilient people.
#survivors #resilience #metoo #thisispublichealth #iampublichealth #sexualviolence #childabuse #fostercare #substanceuse #thisismentalhealth #ptsd #depression #anxiety #ocd #add #si

text:
rising: jonesing (9/14) by nicholas jones, 29 october 2018. -

i’m jonesing for a love-sin,
a ride upon the starlight express,
pain, pride, fire, and dominance,
a chance to lay beneath the stars,
and navigate uncharted territory,
in hopes to find the morning glory,
of waking up right next to you,

but it’s still gonna be how it’s gonna be,
and it’s gonna go the way it’s gonna go, 
so don’t be jonesing for a fix that ain’t never gonna come,
just keep digging your ditch until the day is done,
and when it’s time to say goodbye - pack it all in,
and take it with you when you leave,

he may be jonesing for a dose of you,
but you are not obligated to sustain him,
you are not obligated to abstain from happiness just to please him,
and you’re not lesser than a jester when he’s a clown amidst a carnival,
of stranger-friends and fake happiness,
that beckon to be called - because you are better than them,

and without him ever wearing you down,
he’ll be jonesing all around with nothing left to find,
no tears left to cry - no pain and no shame,
because you don’t need a man to pave your way,
and you don’t need him to take your pain away,

i’m jonesing for a venue - a chance to sound the alarms,
to write love on my arms in the place of broken dreams,
to know what unconditional love really means,
the love of harmony - the jonesing for a dose of self-indulgence,
that being sexy and single and free affords to me,
the softness of my skin and the strength within my bones,

sincerely,
mr. jones. -

text:
rising: dust (10/14) by nicholas jones, 10 november 2018. -

when the evasion of trust,
becomes all too real,
just know that you are more,
than dust in the field,
where memory plays tricks,
with your peace of mind,
and if you believe in yourself,
you will win each time,

when your heart is weak,
just close your eyes,
and imagine this,
being prosperous,
and knowing that half the fight,
of being courageous is,
putting yourself back on your feet,
and rising out of your bed,
each and every morning,

be strong - you’ve got this,
and you know all of the hands,
you’ve been dealt before,
so you can do anything,
if you focus more,
of your precious time,
towards persisting the will,
of the dust to rise,
because the skies are clear,
for you - my dear,

love him,
but let him go,
look to the skies,
and like the fury,
of a saint in a rise,
clear the dust,
from both sides,
of your broken wings,
and learn to fly again,
you’ve got this. -

text:
rising: next to never (11/14) by nicholas jones, 18 september 2018. -

i see the roots of destruction,
and the darkest of clouds,
in the most dangerous weather,
before the brightest suns,
come back around again,
to change my mind,
and i see people changing,
next to never - next to never,

i see the burdens hate can bring,
and it just makes me want to sing,
a song for those who fear the tides,
of love in its most purest form,
so i write songs inside my head,
to face the existential dread,
words of praise for harder days,
but still - people change,
next to never - next to never,

i see the faces of those i once knew,
and i feel proud of how we all grew,
from the shells in which we resided,
now that the hurt has all subsided,
i’m proud of them in spite of pain,
you have to lose to seek to gain,
rain will fall and the sun will rise,
and then one day - we all will die,
but the memories will survive,
next to never - next to never,

i saw jim in a cafe the other day,
and we looked in each other’s eyes,
just so long enough to recognize,
the strands of the purple dreams,
the haze of half a thousand years,
that we left behind - and in all of,
the regret of having left the house,
we parted ways having spoken,
next to never - next to never,

i texted him and told him that i was,
spending my time talking to jesus,
and repenting of my sins thinking,
that somehow it could save him,
and me - from all the sadness that,
surrounded us back then and now,
and maybe we could talk somehow,
next to never - next to never,

and now i’m here growing older,
with each passing day - bolder,
than the one that came before,
and i look back on all those days,
that have passed and still i say,
though i may see you next to never,
i will remember you - always,
i will remember you - always. -

text:
rising: on my way (12/14) by nicholas jones, 31 october 2018. -

for the longest time - i swore that i was falling,
and i didn’t know it then - but i was so blind,
too blind to see that he wasn’t right for me,
so i burned the bridge that i spent so much time building,
to forge a new path - and i’m never looking back,
or at least - that’s exactly what i’m telling myself today,
and i’ll try my best not to fall back into my old temptations,
of saving someone else too far away from saving,
or blaming someone else for my own misbehaving,
and he won’t stop me - because i’m on my way,
to a better place - to brighter days - so look out now - ‘cause i’m on my way. -

or at least - that’s exactly what i’m telling myself today,
and i’ll try my best not to fall back into my old temptations,
of saving someone else too far away from saving,
or blaming someone else for my own misbehaving,
and he won’t stop me - because i’m on my way,
to a better place - to brighter days - so look out now - ‘cause i’m on my way. -

text:
rising: heal me (13/14) by nicholas jones, 01 october 2018. -

put your hands on my body parts - and help me mend this broken heart,
because i need your guidance more than i ever needed what came before,
and i never want to turn away from you - beautiful eyes bursting with truth,
real recognizes real the way that i can recognize you from miles away,
a star was born in the midnight sky the night that i made love to you,
because you bring me to my knees in the form of a praise,
worshipping the promise of better days,
because i know that i can stand beside you,
and everything will be okay - so thank you,
and if you ever need someone - to hold you up against darkened suns,
i’m here - and i will heal you the way that you heal me,
rising and rising and rising and rising - eternally.

b.b. -

text:
rising: ashes to ashes (14/14) by nicholas jones, 02 november 2018.

i miss talking to you sometimes - because you had such a way,
of making things make sense - and paying recompense,
for sins that we committed on another - but never each other,
just two angry kids sitting on curbs outside of bars,
talking about mariah carey and vintage cars,
flipping cigarettes into gutters and watching them sink,
and then so suddenly - we can blink,
and we’re gone forever,

forever can seem so futile in the eyes of cynicism,
you told me that my eyes were prisms,
shooting rays and solar flares from beams,
that captured all of your hopes and dreams,
in human form,

i was afraid of thunderstorms so you’d hold me through the night,
but now i sleep with a light on because i know,
that you’re not coming back this time,
so i close my eyes and hope my mind can take,
me back to a place where i know we both belong,
listening to your favorite song - and watching you laugh,
as i tried so desperately to harmonize,
but then i’d give up frustrated and just hum along the rest of the way,
singing on a sunday always made for better days to follow,
but now you’re gone and the heart is only hollow,
as hollow as the fire of the soul,

so even today when i’m sitting on the pier,
the sweet nothings that you whispered in my ear,
after all this time - are still all that i can hear,
angel grows and your favorite show still plays on a loop,
because it became my favorite too - and i miss you,
in the way that a friend misses his best friend,
because maybe that’s what we should have been,
the whole time that we were together,
time has a way of mending minds,

i miss you so much - and though my words may turn to dust,
i will not interfere - but i’ll open another beer,
and sip it lightly hoping one day you will hear,
the words that fall to this paper as i write them here,
this is how we move forward - this is how to disappear,
ashes to ashes - time passes - and we will carry on,
rising like ashes in a windstorm.

text: in 2006, tarana burke was consumed by a desire to do something about the sexual violence she saw in her community. she took out a piece of paper, wrote “me too” across the top and laid out an action plan for a movement centered on the power of empathy between survivors. more than a decade later, she reflects on what has since become a global movement — and makes a powerful call to dismantle the power and privilege that are building blocks of sexual violence. “we owe future generations nothing less than a world free of sexual violence,” she says. “i believe we can build that world.” #ted #tedx #california #metoo #inspiration #inspirationalquotes

text:
“o #metoo não teria acontecido, se trump não tivesse sido eleito", disse hanna rosin, numa referência ao fortalecimento do movimento feminista nos eua, neste sábado, no festival piauí globonews de jornalismo, em são paulo. hanna é autora do livro the end of men and the rise of women, sobre a proeminência das mulheres em vários segmentos, e ajudou a criar há dez anos a doublex, seção da revista on-line slate sobre o universo feminino, que incluia um podcast, em que a maioria da audiência era masculina. em sua conversa com branca vianna e natuza nery no festival, ela falou sobre como ainda é necessário aprimorar engajamento on-line de movimentos sociais como o #metoo, mas também de sua importância e de como lida com trump sendo mulher, feminista e jornalista - hanna entrevistou sua própria mãe sobre os motivos que a levaram a votar no presidente.

text:
chegamos a 28 semanas com muito amor! 💕
.
.
.

segundo @babycenterbr esta semana, o bebê ultrapassou a barreira de 1kg e pode medir 38cm.
chegamos à reta final, o terceiro e último trimestre da gravidez começa na semana que se inicia agora. o ganho de peso é mais rápido: a maioria das mulheres engorda em média 5kg só neste trimestre.
o bebê abre os olhos e vira a cabeça se perceber uma luz forte fora da barriga. a camada de gordura sob a pele está se formando.
.
.
.

obs.: segundo os especialistas, cada bebê se desenvolve do seu jeito, mesmo dentro do útero. o objetivo destas páginas sobre desenvolvimento fetal é dar uma ideia geral de como o feto cresce dentro da barriga.
.
.
.

o bebê abre os olhos e vira a cabeça se perceber uma luz forte fora da barriga. a camada de gordura sob a pele está se formando.

.
.

dos grandes mentiras de la educación patriarcal con las que nos criaron .

.

eso es ser un criminal

.

.

.

text:
rising: breathe, pt. 1 (4/14) by nicholas jones, 12 september 2018. -

all alone in my room at night - a light still shines as i sit to write,
in a moment of intense romantic reflection,
some words for the boys whom i’ve loved before,
but for one reason or another - i am with no more,
it’s time to breathe - it’s time to set you free,

dear nolan,
i’ve thought about you quite a bit over the last six years,
and to this day - i can remember every conversation we ever had,
from day one - and i always told myself that one day we’d be together,
because you’re everything i’ve always known i’ve always wanted,
and i can’t wait to see you again - whenever you decide to let your heart,
bring you on your way back home to me - i’m always down,

dear timothy,
we loved each other so much - more than either of us could understand,
and we tried so hard to make things work,
but sometimes things happens for reasons that at the time,
may seem unclear - and when i think of all the fallen tears,
between the two of us - that’s when i miss you most,
because the words we used the night i left you,
still ring in my ears after all these years gone by,
and through the passing of time - i’ll pray that the day will come when we find,
peace among the broken pieces - the shards of glass that pervaded our past,
because we both deserve better - and i hope we find it - i hope you find it,

dear john paul,
you taught me to embrace my artistic side,
to be unapologetic in word and form,
to embrace the most beautiful parts of myself,
that i was afraid the world might hate me for,
you taught me not to be ashamed of my impulses,
but i never felt safe in the distance - and it let me down a path of fear,
that i allowed to motivate each decision i made,
and i’m sorry that the price we paid is separate ways,
but i’m always here for you - whenever you should need a friend... continued in pt. 2 -

text:
as i have recently mentioned, i’m slowly reevaluating how i use social media. one thing that i would like to change about this instagram is that i would like to “blog” more about my writing process and what i’m reading. i recently read peluda by @melissalozadaoliva and what i loved about this book is that melissa has true, raw talent that she uses to share her personal story of being a latina and a child of parents who immigrated to the us. through this poetry book melissa writes conceptually around her experience with thick body hair and how that has effected her views of not only femininity but specifically what it means to be a latina woman who is adopting multiple cultures into her identity, being pulled in several directions. as a white woman myself, this book was a great mirror to hold to my own experiences and assumptions. melissa writes with rich narratives and often she is poignant and humorous. please check her out if you’re looking for excellent girl power poetry. ♥️ -
-
-

text:
rising: breathe, pt. 2 (4/14) by nicholas jones, 12 september 2018. -

dear connor,
i miss your smile - the way that you lit up the room,
in all honesty - one of my biggest regrets in life was letting you walk away,
and not saying i loved you too - because i did,
i just wasn’t ready - but i was - because you were everything,
i always knew i always needed - and for the life of me,
i can’t remember why i chose not to see it through,
but i always loved you - and i always will,
and i’m more sorry that i could never show you my true feelings,

dear trenton,
looking back - i now can see that we were just kids then - and i’d like to think that one day,
we could be friends again - but i get that it may take a while - and if we do come around again,
i’ll greet you with a smile - wish you well and be on my way,
and with so many more things left to say - i will carry them to my grave,

and it’s probably for the best that certain things are left unsent,
like all of the times that i was alone with each of you - precious moments spent,
i absorbed each and every second and every smile and every secret,
and i will carry them with me forever - and i hope that you still carry me with you too. -

text:
shout out to my dear friend & fellow baddie @saralanelionlady on the launch of @consentuals.brand 🙌🏻 we hope vivian grows up empowered to stand up for herself and others. thankful to have someone like you in our lives to help give a voice to this cause.
・・・
hi y’all, i’m sara b and the creator of @consentuals.brand . years ago i started pressing panties that said “bomb pussy”. it was a fun and playful way to make people blush and assert my feminist, artistic independence. as the years have gone by i saw the “me too” movement, white feminism, the brett kavanaugh hearings, and pinche trump. my fun quickly turned in to reality and a responsibility to my community, family, friends, and myself. ive spent the last two years processing a lifetime of abusive relationships, self loathing, and sexual assault. consentuals was created as a therapeutic and artistic platform to heal, to be loud, and a place that i could share with whoever wants to participate. i want to thank everyone who has been on this journey with me and everyone who is just now coming along. consentuals are for you and you and you and #metoo 📸 @dearestaly

text:
rising: cosmic connection (5/14) by nicholas jones, 29 december 2017. -

laying next to you feels like mixing moonbeams and daydreams,

like a stream of consciousness unbothered by anything and everything,

beyond your bedroom door - big and blue - the world keeps moving,

but we’re standing still and almost simultaneously you feel me and fill me completely,

and all i really know right now is how much i love laying next to you,

you see right through me the same way that a widow looks through a window,

longing for something that seemed like just a taste,

when compared to what comes next - and i will miss your embrace every time that you’re away,

i’ll think of you each and every day without rest,

you are the calm and the tempest and like a cosmic connection - you line and align,

all of my fears with your lips to gods ears,

and then they desolate like pearls of oceanic salt drifting away one grain at a time,

a night-time walk on the beach beneath the blackest sky,

you are the limits of a limitless abyss across years of darkness - you are the stars - you are the light,

you are the cosmic bliss in blackened skies and the want inside the need to know.

b + d. -

text:
hoje foi dia de pré-natal! 
ouvimos o coraçãozinho da nossa princesinha (papai sempre nos acompanha). ❤
como é emocionante e tranquilizador ouvir, ela estava se mexendo muito e eu não sentindo nada. . - a pressão está ok (90/70).
- estou com 59.250kg - engordei 4.250 até agora.
- fizemos a medição uterina (que serve para avaliar o crescimento do bebê), a minha deu 26cm e estou com 27+3 semanas.
.

estou tomando ácido fólico e sulfato ferroso, vitaminas prescritas pelo médico, e farei os segundos exames laboratoriais para a próxima consulta.
.

estamos muito bem e a mamãe aqui bastante ansiosa para conhecer essa princesinha! 👸💕
.
.
.
.

text:
life.... 🧘🏼‍♀️ almost 5 years ago i became a mumma to a little girl at 18 it was a challenge but i managed. when you become a mum it’s like you become a superhero and you would do anything to make sure your children were safe and loved. 
18 was also the age i left victoria to flee a horrible, toxic abusive relationship that i had been stuck in for 3 years... i didn’t get a childhood that was stolen from me and so was the choice of when i lost my innocence. i really wish i knew at 15 what i know now and had the confidence to speak out earlier then i did but then i wouldn’t be a mother now and i wouldn’t be in the same place as now. these are my scars but not my definition.... it’s hard to understand how a 15 year old can be in a “abusive” relationship but this is why i have decided to start to speak up about my abuse to stop the mentality that it’s not abuse if one is under a certain age or if they are both young... these habits start young. #metoo #letsstandup

text:
how do you reconnect with yourself, your dreams and your hopes?  i reconnect when i visit the ocean (as i did the week of thanksgiving). i feel so aligned when i am near “my water”. i also connect by journaling and exploring what it is that i am really wanting.  i then use my planner to figure out how to put together the steps towards making it happen. 
i find co-regulating with those who support me in working towards making my hopes and dreams a reality to be essential and beneficial.  they are so uplifting for me to spend time with.

make a list of ways you can reconnect with yourself, your hope, and your dreams.  then break it down into smaller steps that you can work on until you make it all your reality.  it is possible! 💜

text:
my favorite message form church today was from from president larsen.
.
when looking at a small newborn child, have you ever wondered how you could love them so much?
.
we don’t love them because of their accomplishments or the things they’re good at. they haven’t yet accomplished anything. on the contrary, they poop on us, they spit up on us & they cause us to lose sleep, but yet we love them. why?
.
because they are ours! there is no other reason. they are ours and the love is real.
.
our heavenly father does not love us because of our accomplishments or the things we are good at. we don’t have to prove ourselves to him. he loves us simply because we are his! #asoulsurvivorspiritual

text:
press release: announcing duchess international magazine print copy launch!

for immediate release
november 22, 2018

yes! we’ve got great news and we’re super excited to share!

duchess international magazine is proud to announce the launch of her maiden print edition –‘the magnificent woman’, on sunday, 9th december 2018 at the grand ibis hotel, ikeja, lagos.

the initiative, driven by the need to improve the reading experience of our esteemed readers will provide well grounded information on lifestyle, health and wellness and fashion. 
we’ve got an interesting lineup of events: enlightening discussions, networking opportunities and high profile personalities in attendance.

outstanding individuals who have done well in their chosen fields will be honoured as well.

notable speakers and guest at the event include; dr. elishama ideh, ms. yemisi jenkins mbe, ms. bisola munis and a host of others.

let’s root for each other and watch one another grow. magnificent women we all are!

don’t be left out. save the date!

text:
same person, different lifestyle. left side living a life to other people's expectations➖ right side, i choose to be happy and live my own life, not the life others want me to.
_________________________________
way too many people are living a life that is not theirs to live. they live their lives according to what others think is best for them, they live their lives according to what their parents think it`s best for them, to what their friends, their enemies and their teachers, their government and the media thinks it`s best for them. they ignore their inner voice, that inner calling. they are so busy with pleasing everybody, with living up to other people’s expectations, that they lose control over their lives. they forget what makes them happy, what they want, what they need….and eventually, they forget about themselves.  you have one life – this one right now – you must live it, own it, and especially don’t let other people’s opinions distract you from your path. dare to give up living your life to other people’s expectations and start living it your way instead.
name: Amanda Essen WEAK TO STRONG

text: shout out to all the moms out there juggling already full calendars on the second day of the month. shout out to the moms out there who are making time for themselves to go to lunch with girlfriends, even if that means showing up an hour late because you’re bickering with your husband between nursing a clingy baby. shout out to all the moms out there with the car literally so full of all their kids’ shit they could survive a week living out of just the car alone. shout out to all the moms out there who spilled their coffee while they’re driving because their front seats are so full of purses and diaper bags and evidence of your full, chaotic and blessed life. shout out to all the moms out there who were waiting for the last day the month put gas in their car, so they didn’t go anywhere for a whole three days. shout out to the moms out there who are hurting, grieving, trying to find joy in a season that supposed to be joyful but feels mostly sad, stressful, or just without something/someone we wish were here. i see you. i am you. there is room for you at my table. we’re just gonna have to clear off a space amongst the markers and craft supplies from three days ago. and hang up that sweater still laying on the chair from yesterday. but please come sit at my table. coffee is always on, and the judgement and expectations are always off.
name: ☀️🍋Cori Kish🍋☀️

text:
￼subscribe

metoo? guess it doesn't apply to big ben (column)

mike argento |margento@ydr.com | 8:31 am est january 10, 2018 ￼ ￼ ￼ ￼ ￼

as the #metoo campaign continues to grow, well-known women in the york community join their voices and share their stories.

jason plotkin, york daily record

the other day, just as the me too movement was enjoying a deserved day in the spotlight after the golden globe awards, i got an email from a reader who raised a pretty good question. 
he had watched as just about every other sentient human with a y chromosome had been pilloried and shamed and stripped of their livelihoods for being, well, pigs and doing things that civilized human beings should not have to be told not to do, and he wondered about another bearer of the wild-hair gene who had apparently escaped nearly unscathed from the consequences of his deplorable actions. ￼

other guys accused of acting terribly toward women lost their gigs. this guy gets a trophy.

the reader was wondering why pittsburgh steelers quarterback ben roethlisberger has not faced the same kind of consequences as the likes of harvey weinstein, kevin spacey, matt lauer, al franken, charlie rose and louis c.k. 
and i thought, #metoo. 
more: sexual harassment is not just a hollywood problem (column)

as you may recall, roethlisberger, poised to make another run at the super bowl as the steelers open post-season play sunday, had been accused of sexual assault by two women, one in 2009 and the other in 2010. 
the woman who accused him in 2009 filed a civil suit, which was later settled out of court. the other accuser, who told police that roethlisberger had raped her in a bathroom stall at a georgia bar, an accusation supported by statements three of her friends gave police, asked that the case not be prosecuted, concerned that a trial would be "a very intrusive personal experience." the district attorney declined to file charges and announced as much. 
still, the nfl suspended roethlisberger for six games, later reduced to four. he went on to lead the steelers to the super bowl that year, losing to the green bay packers.
name: James Mcmillan

the woman who accused him in 2009 filed a civil suit, which was later settled out of cou. the other accuser, who told police that roethlisberger had raped her in a bathroom stall at a georgia bar, an accusation suppoed by statements three of her friends gave police, asked that the case not be prosecuted, concerned that a trial would be "a very intrusive personal experience." the district attorney declined to file charges and announced as much. 
still, the nfl suspended roethlisberger for six games, later reduced to four. he went on to lead the steelers to the super bowl that year, losing to the green bay packers.

text:
if being raped wasn't traumatic enough in itself, what's even worse is what people sometimes say to victims of rape. here, vanessa, a survivor herself, relays some of the actual things that people have said to her... and what it does to you.

according to @sophiabush "asking what someone was wearing when they were assaulted is like asking someone what outfit they had on when they were robbed. it doesn't matter. it's a violation that was done to them, not because of them." it's #notokay to victim blame. 
it's #notokay to show no sensitivity to victims. your words have power. .

jak przypadło wam do gustu nagano 98? co do treści kawałka - coraz częściej widzę, że ludzie traktują innych, i co gorsza siebie, przedmiotowo. często ja, czy moje koleżanki spotykamy się z komentarzami  pod zdjęciami (nawet komercyjnymi) w bieliźnie, że najładniej powiedziane - nie szanujemy się. a to przecież tylko praca, która ma przedstawić produkt i to tylko ciało! które każdy z nas ma w większym lub mniejszym stopniu podobne. nie oceniam, sama nie jestem idealna, ale zapewne te same osoby, które wyzywają gorszące odsłonięcie brzucha, być może zdradzają swoich ukochanych, obgadują przyjaciółki, bawią się relacjami zupełnie jakby to był jakiś tetris. szanujcie siebie, swoje umysły i ciała, każdy ma uczucia. #mycalvins #metoo ⠀

text:
erster winterlauf ....
als wir los gestartet sind, war es trocken, regen hat gerade pause angelegt, wind 🌬 aber nicht und  irgendwann hat sich auch  der regen zurück gemeldet. und somit waren die letzte 5 km als dusche angenommen, hat nur die seife gefällt...🙈😁
abends konnte wir noch livemusik genießen, unsere große spielte erstmal in quartett und danach im orchester 🎼🎶🎵🎻🥰
du bist toll mein schatz @maegi.1002 und wir sind sehr stolz auf dich 😘
🕯 brennt  natürlich auch🤩 
guten start in die neue woche und bleibt fit ✌🏼👱🏻‍♀️
*******************************
первый зимний забег с группой беганутых....
когда мы стартовали, дождь делал передышку, но ветер 🌬 нет и в скоре дождь опять дал о себе знать, и зарядил полной силой. 🌧последние 5 км бежали как под душем, 🚿нахватало только мыла 🧼🙈😁...
вечером мы насладились живой музыкой, наше старшенькое чудо выступало в квартете и в оркестре 🎵🎶🎼🎻🥰
ну и конечно была зажженная первая 🕯, время отсчёта началось 🤩🙌🏻
всем хорошей недели и оставайтесь в движении ✌🏼👱🏻‍♀️
*******************************

text:
we met heather at a local house party where she sang and gave me goosebumps. then she played at our wedding and i cried 💕 
heather is a social-justice songwriter and mental health activist on a mission to make the world a more inclusive place! 💕

her new collection of songs are centered around the theme...finding the light in the struggle. ✨ 
i am so proud of her and can’t wait for her to share her songs. empowering those who are in the struggle. there needs to be more music about mental health!! ✨

i live with the last thought that went through my mind...the words i didn’t speak...asking a friend, “are you ok?” u ok spoke to me in sweden. i think about it all the time. we don’t know what someone might be struggling with on the inside. it can be invisible to the eyes. we need to be more aware.✨ you can be a part of glimmer and help heather mae make this new record! ✨💕 @heathermaemusic please watch the video in her bio. help if you can. share if you don’t mind 💕
.
.

text:
fortsättningen på #metoo är feministisk politik 
#metoo-kampanjen har satt ljuset på omfattningen av det sexuella våldet mot kvinnor. – det hoppingivande med #metoo är att det som feminister berättat om i decennier blir tydligt för flera: vi lever fortfarande i ett patriarkalt samhälle och det skapar strukturella problem i alla våra relationer, från de mest intima och ut i de samhälleliga. vi behöver en ny kultur i politiken där vi definierar makt som något annat än strävan efter kontroll och dominans. vi behöver sociala reformer, skärpt lagstiftning, omfördelning av ekonomiska resurser och en politik som på allvar erkänner att kvinnors rättigheter är mänskliga rättigheter. fortsättningen på #metoo är feministisk politik, säger gudrun schyman.

text:
dastu was 14 years old when her uncle started molesting her dastu was raised by a single mother her father abandoned them when she was a baby dastus mum use to go to work early in the morning she use to leave her daughter with her younger brother to look after her while she goes to works all day he use to take & bring her back from school dastu got very sick one day her uncle calls his sister saying meet us at the hospital the doctor says she had a miscarriage and she will need a surgery dastus mum over hears her brother telling the doctor am her husband and do everything necessary also to not let anyone else know our marriage is still a secret dastus mum being in denial couldn't believe what she heard the moment her brother saw his sister he ran away dastu recovered and slowly got back to being to her old self but somehow both dastu and her mother weren't the same after that incident

text:
part two: life lessons ✌🏽
control, it is something that we all try to hold on to even if we don’t consciously realize it. trying to control every aspect of our lives, mapping out the perfect route to our success ✨ •
however, as all of you know, we simply cannot control everything in our lives. sometimes things happen that we can’t  plan for and it can throw a huge wrench in our perceived path. instead of thinking of this as the end, think of this as an opportunity to create 👣
•
in times like these, we have to remember that we do still have a choice for control. we can choose how we react to the situation, we can choose to either let it control us or let it teach us...not matter how horrifying the experience 🧘‍♀️
•
at first it was hard for me to find a lesson in what happened. i was angry, scared, hurt, and felt like i had lost all control. slowly, i realized, there were lessons to be learned. despite what happened, i can give the world more love than i ever have ❤️ • 
to love despite the hate in the world 🗺 • 
to educate and spread awareness despite the ignorance in the world 🧠 • 
to remember everyone is fighting a battle you know nothing about ⚔️ • 
what happened is not my fault and i did not “ask for it” or “let it happen” 🤐 • 
i forgive my attacker for what they did.  no, i do not condone it and i believe they should pay for their actions, but i refuse to hold onto the hate and the anger. i will continue to love and fight for what is right but i will do it from my hart.  i will not steep to the level of my abuser and use my actions to cause harm or raise hate 💕 
#beyourownhero #metoo #love

text:
interview pour elle :
invitée à s’exprimer à l’occasion d’une table ronde organisée par « the hollywood reporter », lady gaga a livré un témoignage glaçant sur le harcèlement et l’agression sexuelle dont elle a été victime alors qu’elle n’était âgée que de 19 ans.

quand j’ai commencé dans le business de la musique à l’âge de 19 ans, c’était la règle, pas l’exception, d’arriver dans un studio d’enregistrement et de se faire harceler », raconte-t-elle. « c’était juste normal, donc je regrette ne pas avoir parlé plus tôt. j’en ai finalement parlé, en disant aux gens autour de moi que j’avais été agressée quand j’étais jeune. »

elle raconte également regretter la culture de solidarité masculine qui plane autour des agresseurs. « personne ne veut perdre son pouvoir, donc on ne vous protège pas parce que s’ils disent quelque chose, cela leur enlève un peu de pouvoir », ajoute-t-elle. « ce que j’espère, c’est que ces conversations seront entendues, il ne s’agit pas que de l’égalité salariale d’un côté… d’un traitement égal de l'autre, et ensuite des agressions. mais ils s’agit de tout en même temps, et ce mouvement s’intéresse à tout cela », a-t-elle souligné, faisant référence à #metoo.

aujourd’hui, la chanteuse confie qu’elle souffre toujours de stress post-traumatique lié à son agression survenue il y a 13 ans. elle continue à en combattre les symptômes.

#ladygaga #ladygagaweb

text: so this girl turned 29 years young last week! time sure does fly but that's okay because this is my year! i have been through a lifetime of pain, some of which some people may never experience. i have had my ups and downs. battled and still battling depression and anxiety each day. i've made plenty of mistakes along the way, i'm not perfect. at one point i played victim and felt sorry for myself but then i realized that all of my experiences and mistakes made me stronger. thankfully, i have a supportive and loving husband who turned my life around the moment i met him. we too have had our moments and worked through them making our marriage even stronger. so when ever you're feeling like your at your all time low think to yourself what can i learn from this and make sure to tell yourself each day that you are strong and you can handle anything thrown at you! #innerstrength #innerpeace #forgiveness #forgiveyourself #depressionawareness #anxietyawareness #bestrong #metoo #metoomovement #strongerthanhate #strongerthanever #thisisme #cheersto29 #thankfulforlife #veganlife #veganlifestyle #birthdaybabe #cheerstoanotheryear #marriage #lovemyhusband

@regrann from @warif_ng: day 8 | december 02 
sexual consent is an agreement to participate in sexual activity between two adults (over the legal age of 18). it is a vital concept that needs to be understood when it comes to intimate relations between men and women as it must be freely given, reversible, informed, enthusiastic and specific. when there is no consent, it is sexual violation or rape.

if you are forced to have sex against your will, if you say no, asleep, unconscious, under the influence of alcohol or a controlled drug or substance - you cannot give your consent and you have been sexually assaulted.

no means no! hear word! .

text:
i have heard feminism defined as everything from ‘the belief that all people are equal’ to ‘feminists believe that women should be the same as men in society.’ what? nah.

feminism is not ‘for the equality of all people’. feminism is not ‘the belief that women should be treated the same as men.’ feminism is not ‘the movement to make women equal to men in society.’ feminism is not equalism.

for women to be valid, whole human beings in society – feminism has got to move beyond this notion that women are striving for what men already have. i don’t want anything men already have. none of it. it’s a mess. 
feminism is the liberation of women and girls all over the world from the patriarchy and misogyny that continues to harm and oppress them as a class of people. feminism centres women unflinchingly and unapologetically. feminism is the conversation about women’s issues in the world; without having to add some tokenistic sentence at the end acknowledging that men also experience some things too. yah, we know. but we are talking about women right now, so hush. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
❤️
i am a true believer
the universe is on my side 
today i saw it 
with my own eyes..
the house where i once faced evil
was nowhere to be found
30 years later it had vanished 
just like i dreamed about..
they replaced it with a new home
torn the old one completely down
i recognized its shell
but there was nothing left there anymore
for me to be scared about..
home to a new family
and even though it’s on the same ground
it felt so very peaceful
with kids playing around..
i am a true believer
the universe is on my side
today she winked at me
and as i understood her message 
i stepped into the future 
where everything is bright
🙏

text:
死ぬほど素晴らしい！　アガサ・クリスティ原作「無実はさいなむ」ドラマ版

news海外ドラマnavi｜ 2018.04.12 
https://dramanavi.net/news/2018/04/post-6876.php

死ぬほど素晴らしい！　アガサ・クリスティ原作「無実はさいなむ」ドラマ版 "ミステリの女王"アガサ・クリスティによる1958年の小説「無実はさいなむ」を英bbcが映像化したドラマ『 #ordealbyinnocence（原題）』が、イギリスのミステリ愛好家たちに好評だ。3話構成のフーダニット（犯人を当てる形式の推理モノ）で、4月1日から毎週一話ずつ放送されている。一度は放送中止の危機に見舞われたものの、一部のキャストを入れ替えての再撮影を敢行し、イースター・シーズンに無事お披露目となった。 【関連記事】英bbcがクリスティ作品7本をドラマ化！エルキュール・ポアロのあの事件も... ◆1年前の殺人事件は解決しておらず、真犯人はここにいる？

1954年のクリスマスからストーリーは始まる。資産家のレイチェルが自身の邸宅で何者かに殺害され、彼女と一緒に暮らしていた多くの養子たちの一人であり、金銭面で困窮していたジャックに容疑がかけられる。ジャックは無実を主張するも、獄中で死亡する。

1年後、レイチェルを亡くした夫のリオは再婚を決意し、親戚を招いた結婚式を開く。そこへ、ジャックのアリバイを証明できると主張するキャルガリ博士が登場したことで、一同の祝賀ムードは一変する。警察の捜査は誤りで、レイチェル殺しの真犯人は自分たちの中に潜んでいるのだろうか？

レイチェル役に『the hour　裏切りのニュース』のアンナ・チャンセラー、夫のリオ役に『ラブ・アクチュアリー』のビル・ナイを迎え、家族の一人として『ダウントン・アビー』のマシュー・グードも登場する。イギリスの名優ぞろいの作品となっており、深みのある演技は必見だ。 ◆スキャンダルによる危機に素早く対応

本作は、2015年に「そして誰もいなくなった」、 2016年には「検察側の証人」と、同じくクリスティの原作を元としたドラマで脚本を執筆したサラ・フェルプスが引き続き脚本を担当し、2017年のクリスマスにオンエアされる予定だった。しかし、養子の一人であるミッキーを演じていたエド・ウェストウィック（『ゴシップガール』）に性的暴行疑惑が浮上したことから、12月の放映は見送られることに。当人は容疑を否認するも、プロデューサーが彼を外して再撮影する判断を下した。この判断について、telegraph紙は、性的被害を告発する「#metoo」運動の高まりを受けた賢明な対応だったと評価している。

エドの代役を務めたのはクリスチャン・クック（『アート・オブ・モア　美と欲望の果て』）で、キャストは2018年1月に再集結し、12日間にわたって撮影のやり直しに挑んだ。guardian紙は、7月という舞台設定ながらよく見ると白い吐息が確認できるシーンがあると指摘している。 ◆緻密な推理とダークな人間模様に酔いしれる

困難を乗り越えて放送にこぎ着けた甲斐があり、視聴者の反応は好意的だ。ミステリだけあって「"死ぬほど"素晴らしかった」との声や、イースターのtv番組の中で断トツだという評価がtwitter上で出ている。また、翌週の放送が待ちきれない、と3夜連続でないのをもどかしく感じるファンもいるようだ。ビル・ナイは、誰が真犯人なのかを推理して楽しんでほしいとコメントしている。

そんな中、序盤はやや退屈で難解にも感じられたとしているのがtelegraph紙。時間が前後に飛ぶことや、外見のよく似た登場人物が多いことが理由のようだが、ストーリーは折り紙つきで、第1話の終わりまでにはしっかりと心を掴まれたと評価している。本作では、モルヒネ中毒やアルコール依存症などの問題を抱えた一族が放つ暗い雰囲気が、お互いが疑心暗鬼に陥るミステリ特有の緊迫感を助長している。ソリッドな推理のロジックに加え、ダークな心理ドラマも見ものだ。（海外ドラマnavi）

#アガサクリスティ
#agathachristie
#無実はさいなむ
#イギリスbbc で放送されてから、いつ日本で放送されるか待ち遠しく、日本での放送を待ち望んでいました❤❤
この作品はテレビドラマの #ミスマープル で視聴しました。
#そして誰もいなくなった
#検察側の証人
も楽しめましたので、この作品も期待しています。
@officialagathachristie
hashtags: #OrdealByInnocence（原題）』が、イギリスのミステリ愛好家たちに好評だ。3話構成のフーダニット（犯人を当てる形式の推理モノ）で、4月1日から毎週一話ずつ放送されている。一度は放送中止の危機に見舞われたものの、一部のキャストを入れ替えての再撮影を敢行し、イースター・シーズンに無事お披露目となった。, #アガサクリスティ, #AgathaChristie, #無実はさいなむ, #イギリスBBC, #ミスマープル, #そして誰もいなくなった, #検察側の証人

stop_filter_tweet: 死ぬほど素晴らしい！ アガサ・クリスティ原作「無実はさいなむ」ドラマ版 news海外ドラマnavi｜ 2018.04.12 死ぬほど素晴らしい！ アガサ・クリスティ原作「無実はさいなむ」ドラマ版 `` ミステリの女王 '' アガサ・クリスティによる1958年の小説「無実はさいなむ」を英bbcが映像化したドラマ『 【関連記事】英bbcがクリスティ作品7本をドラマ化！エルキュール・ポアロのあの事件も ... ◆1年前の殺人事件は解決しておらず、真犯人はここにいる？ 1954年のクリスマスからストーリーは始まる。資産家のレイチェルが自身の邸宅で何者かに殺害され、彼女と一緒に暮らしていた多くの養子たちの一人であり、金銭面で困窮していたジャックに容疑がかけられる。ジャックは無実を主張するも、獄中で死亡する。 1年後、レイチェルを亡くした夫のリオは再婚を決意し、親戚を招いた結婚式を開く。そこへ、ジャックのアリバイを証明できると主張するキャルガリ博士が登場したことで、一同の祝賀ムードは一変する。警察の捜査は誤りで、レイチェル殺しの真犯人は自分たちの中に潜んでいるのだろうか？ レイチェル役に『the hour 裏切りのニュース』のアンナ・チャンセラー、夫のリオ役に『ラブ・アクチュアリー』のビル・ナイを迎え、家族の一人として『ダウントン・アビー』のマシュー・グードも登場する。イギリスの名優ぞろいの作品となっており、深みのある演技は必見だ。 ◆スキャンダルによる危機に素早く対応 本作は、2015年に「そして誰もいなくなった」、 2016年には「検察側の証人」と、同じくクリスティの原作を元としたドラマで脚本を執筆したサラ・フェルプスが引き続き脚本を担当し、2017年のクリスマスにオンエアされる予定だった。しかし、養子の一人であるミッキーを演じていたエド・ウェストウィック（『ゴシップガール』）に性的暴行疑惑が浮上したことから、12月の放映は見送られることに。当人は容疑を否認するも、プロデューサーが彼を外して再撮影する判断を下した。この判断について、telegraph紙は、性的被害を告発する「etoo」運動の高まりを受けた賢明な対応だったと評価している。 エドの代役を務めたのはクリスチャン・クック（『アート・オブ・モア 美と欲望の果て』）で、キャストは2018年1月に再集結し、12日間にわたって撮影のやり直しに挑んだ。guardian紙は、7月という舞台設定ながらよく見ると白い吐息が確認できるシーンがあると指摘している。 ◆緻密な推理とダークな人間模様に酔いしれる 困難を乗り越えて放送にこぎ着けた甲斐があり、視聴者の反応は好意的だ。ミステリだけあって「 '' 死ぬほど '' 素晴らしかった」との声や、イースターのtv番組の中で断トツだという評価がtwitter上で出ている。また、翌週の放送が待ちきれない、と3夜連続でないのをもどかしく感じるファンもいるようだ。ビル・ナイは、誰が真犯人なのかを推理して楽しんでほしいとコメントしている。 そんな中、序盤はやや退屈で難解にも感じられたとしているのがtelegraph紙。時間が前後に飛ぶことや、外見のよく似た登場人物が多いことが理由のようだが、ストーリーは折り紙つきで、第1話の終わりまでにはしっかりと心を掴まれたと評価している。本作では、モルヒネ中毒やアルコール依存症などの問題を抱えた一族が放つ暗い雰囲気が、お互いが疑心暗鬼に陥るミステリ特有の緊迫感を助長している。ソリッドな推理のロジックに加え、ダークな心理ドラマも見ものだ。（海外ドラマnavi） ガサクリスティ gathachristie 実はさいなむ で放送されてから、いつ日本で放送されるか待ち遠しく、日本での放送を待ち望んでいました❤❤ この作品はテレビドラマの で視聴しました。 して誰もいなくなった 察側の証人 も楽しめましたので、この作品も期待しています。

text:
•
i want to apologise.
i’m sorry i touched you without asking if it’s ok.
•
i’ve always thought that hands-on assists in asana practice is super important. i love (both as a student and teacher) to be close and physical in the asana because it makes me feel more safe and supported as a student, and as the teacher i want the student to feel the same.
and so, when i was about to teach classes i used to, through a little laugh, say “if you don’t appreciate hands-on assists, you’ve come to the wrong class because i use my hands a lot!”
i deeply, deeply apologise for that arrogant, selfish and totally inconsiderate attitude. i am sorry i took the right to put my hands on you without asking, even stating that you basically have no choice than to maybe get my hands on you.
as if i’m not familiar with the disgusting sensation of being touched when i don’t want to.
as if my space haven’t been intruded to.
as if i have never been robbed of the very right to my own body.
as if yoga in any way, shape or form is spared from the same issues as anything else that has to do with... well, people.
•
nowadays i ask for consent. i have the students close their eyes in the beginning and focus on their breath and relax on to their mat, and then i say “if anyone is simply not in a mood for any reason to get hands-on assists today, please raise your arm so i can see it clearly, and i won’t put my hands on you.”
i know that’s not optimal, because i’m actually asking for those who don’t want to be touched to tell me, and that is like saying that being touched is the default, which is n-o-t the case. not anywhere, ever. i should be asking “you who are ok to be touched today, let me know”, because then you’ve set the default to that i don’t touch unless you’ve told me it’s ok.
so, i’m gonna make myself some consent cards, a-fucking-sap. and i urge every yoga teacher to do the same; help change the norm of touching as always being ok, because “it’s yoga”, because that’s just crazy.
and i don’t have to explain why, right?
or do you disagree? please share your thoughts on this! as a student and/or teacher.
•
and again; to all of you who i’ve put my hands on without asking: i’m sorry.

text:
// mais où sont les papas sur instagram…??? (2/2) //
.
mais que je suis heureux d’avoir découvert tout ça, que je suis serein dans ma position de papa. nveo, dme, allaitement, recherche d’autonomie de l’enfant, bienveillance… je constate au quotidien les bienfaits de ces outils sur notre fille.

alors où sont les papas ? dans l’ombre et l’anonymat ? sur les comptes insta de porsche, d’emilie raja… rata… rajow… ski, de dan bilzerian, de guy savoy, de jeff bezos et du psg ? moi aussi je les suis ces comptes chargés en testostérone (sauf le psg, je n’aime pas le foot) !!! mais pas que : j’en suis d’autres aussi. la parentalité, mon enfant, mes enfants m’intéressent et j’apprends plein de trucs grâce à vous, vos publications, celles de vos pairs. 
alors à toutes ces femmes qui publient, qui font bouger les choses, qui ont permis à l’allaitement de revenir en force (même s’il reste du chemin à parcourir !), à la dme de percer, à #metoo de faire trembler les mâles infâmes, à tasjoui d’atteindre les 200k d’abonnés en quelque semaines, etc : faites venir les papas, les moitiés, les hommes qui vous accompagnent ! les combats féminins se gagneront plus facilement si les hommes apparaissent. et je pense que plein d’hommes sont prêts à franchir le pas et vous soutenir, en pleine lumière !

a vos moitiés ! prêtes ? partez !

text:
reminder: it’s ok to not be ok. in 2011 a news segment aired, reporting on the 60 year sentence that my attacker received after brutally raping and beating me. the news anchor described me during the trial: “20 years of covering court trials and i don’t think i’ve ever seen a rape victim this calm, this poised, this strong. was able to look her rapist in the eye and said you did this. now you’re going to pay.” the title of the news segment: “rape victim refuses to be broken”
•
following the trial i felt that my life had to mirror this public persona. the truth: i was broken, and silently struggling in my private life with shame and guilt from my assault. was it my fault for allowing this stranger into my car? was it my fault for drinking that night?
•
additionally, making it to trial was a two year court process, in which my attacker was able to continue (or postpone) our trial eight times. that meant 8 times i had to meet with my attorney, listen to taped statements, go over depositions, and practice cross-examination. that meant 8 times i had to relive every graphic detail of that night, over and over and over again.
•
when i wasn’t dealing with trial or trying to put on a facade of being “perfect”, i was suffering in silence. i thought that to reveal my emotions and my mess would equate weakness. so i kept it to myself and buried it far below the surface, then relied on alcohol to completely numb and disassociate from the pain. the news anchors’ words couldn’t be more spot on: i refused to be broken.
•
but i soon found that when you bury and suppress your trauma, that trauma eventually finds a way to speak out loud in your life. for me, it was eating disorders, suicidality, mental health issues, addiction, & violence.
•
when i changed my perspective:
that it was ok to not be strong,
that it was ok to admit that i was weak,
that it was ok to ask for support,
that is was ok to meet my pain with empathy and acceptance...
that’s when i realized that my brokenness made me better, not necessarily “stronger.”
•
this message is for anyone running from your raw, fucked up, painful mess. stop running, stand in it, own it, welcome it...& it’ll make you better 💛

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text: please believe survivors. statistics prove that false accusations are marginal compared to real ones. it’s just hard to accept that rape happens all the time, so we try to deny it. and here’s the thing about “evidence”: i’ve survived some minor cases of sexual assault. i don’t remember every detail. i have no physical objects that would help me “prove” anything. one of the memories was repressed for so long i was confused about where it occurred. but here’s the thing: it did. #ibelievesurvivors #ibelieveher #rape #rapeculture #metoo #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #feminist #activist

text:
i believe mary and elizabeth should be believed.

luke 1:26-38
26 in the sixth month of elizabeth’s pregnancy, god sent the angel gabriel to nazareth, a village in galilee, 27 to a virgin named mary. she was engaged to be married to a man named joseph, a descendant of king david. 28 gabriel appeared to her and said, “greetings, favored woman! the lord is with you!” 29 confused and disturbed, mary tried to think what the angel could mean. 30 “don’t be afraid, mary,” the angel told her, “for you have found favor with god! 31 you will conceive and give birth to a son, and you will name him jesus. 32 he will be very great and will be called the son of the most high. the lord god will give him the throne of his ancestor david. 33 and he will reign over israel forever; his kingdom will never end!” 34 mary asked the angel, “but how can this happen? i am a virgin.” 35 the angel replied, “the holy spirit will come upon you, and the power of the most high will overshadow you. so the baby to be born will be holy, and he will be called the son of god. 36 what’s more, your relative elizabeth has become pregnant in her old age! people used to say she was barren, but she has conceived a son and is now in her sixth month. 37 for nothing is impossible with god.”
38 mary responded, “i am the lord’s servant. may everything you have said about me come true.” and then the angel left her.

text:
patricia hearts fue una rica heredera secuestrada por el ejercito smbiones de liberacion. la sorpresa llegó cuando el esl anuncio que patricia se había unido a sus filas y este hecho se confirmó en el asalto del banco hibernia al captarse una imagen de patricia entre sus asaltantes.
este mismo año,2018, patricia ha conseguido paralizar la filmación de una película sobre su vida. "no es ningún secreto que fui secuestrada, violada y torturada cuando tenía 19 años. romantizar lo que me sucedió y definirlo como una animadisima aventura sería negar que lo que me sucedió fue destruir a una niña por dentro y por fuera. en un momento en el que el movimiento #metoo ha logrado tantos progresos para demostrar lo que le sucede a las víctimas del abuso y maltrato, no se debe banalizar algo así" 
el juicio contra patricia hearst, los  psicólogos argumentaron que patricia había sido víctima del síndrome de estocolmo, un trastorno de adaptación por el cual los secuestrados se alían con los captores. el tribunal no aceptó estas alegaciones y la condenó a la cárcel. pero en 2001, cuando la psicología aceptaba unánimemente la existencia del trastorno, jimmy carter  concedió la libertad condicional a patricia.en el 2001 clinton le concedió el indulto.
el síndrome de estocolmo doméstico explica por qué las mujeres víctimas de abuso psicológico o físico tienen a defender o a seguir con sus maltratadores. de forma inconsciente piensan que así se protegen, al alinearse con ellos. 📗 de esto habla, entre otras cosas "por qué el amor nos duele tanto", una novela. versión digital amazon 4,99 euros. en papel en librerías si la encargas. si la quieres firmada y dedicada por navidad me escribes a comproeselibroya@gmail.com.
#psicologia #resiliencia #eresloquesuperas #feminismo
