text:
i was floored to find such accurate & universally resonating description of harassment on the 6th page of this book itself. i urge everyone to read:
🍂🍁
"why couldn't i not just tell this man to leave  me alone? i didn't have these thoughts until later, and i don't mean an hour later. i mean twenty years later. at 18, i had no proper understanding of the ways that constituted encroachment. i had a feeling for them, an intution, a sense of repugnance for some situations & some people, but i did not know i had a right not to like, not to have to put up with anybody & everybody coming near. best i could manage was to hope the person concerned would hurry up, say whatever they wanted to say & go away, or else to go away myself, politetly & quickly, the very moment i could."
.🍁🍂
most of us have never been taught how to react when faced with physical/verbal assualt. instead since childhood we've been groomed to be polite & obedient, especially to those older. and even if sometimes we do tell what happened, we are expected to not to mention it again to others & "just forget it". all this leads to us feeling shame rather than those who should be ashamed. this is why the next time, we don't speak up and then years later when we do find the courage, we are questioned,"why now?"
.☘️
so, i urge everyone to talk about it and to listen, but most of all i urge parents or would-be parents to talk to their kids - at age 5, 10, 13, 17. please don't think they are too young to get it. you won't be protecting their innocence but protecting those who might try to take it away. this talk is the most difficult but it is also the most important. this generation has a duty to stop #metoo & start #neverme. please pass this message along to as many people as you can.🌻
.
also, i'm beginning to see why this book won the man booker prize this year. can't wait to read it further & do a full review.☘️
.
.
.

text:
#jagtänkerpå  #jagäråretsjulkort 
#jagäråretssammanfattning ——————————————————————— enligt traditionen, så är första advent starten för julsäsongen. även i år, skickar jesuis julkort, som en påminnelse om hur viktigt det är att vi ska tänka på varandra och vissa varandra att vi finns. 
i år till mina 8 vänner på regeringskansliet, gör jesuis en egen analys av året som gick. sammanfattat i några få rader, som vi fick utav varandra sen fjolårets julkortsutskick.
—————————————————————— vänsterpartiet: ännu ett år vi fick, med något färre dickpicks. #metoo fortsatt därän, men nä…ingen mer makt fanns där. när sen september kom, så s slutligen dumpa oss. ———————————————————————— miljöpartiet:  en hårt regeringsmakt vi fick, med ett riktigt miljöavtal så fint. glömde vi bort att titta på. svenskarna som då, grät över ett bensinpris som slog så väldigt hårt, så fler plånbokshål de såg.
——————————————————————-
socialdemokraterna:  en tur med makt, satt allt som ett smack…men ack så kostsam. för att i centrum nå och stå, och se
j. björklund spela svår. ——————————————————————- liberalerna:  ett år, som slutade så i katastrof, att se alla andra gå, och själv tveksamt se på. utan att veta vart man själv står. ——————————————————————— centerpartiet:  så som det gick, och all makt gick mot politikens mitt, med både svek och hög lön, vi hyllade annie lööf. ——————————————————————— kristdemokraterna:  med den kärleksflört vi fick, ett konservativt block vi så gärna tog gift. en sprucken allians, vi inte längre känner för längre är sann. —————————————————————— moderaterna: 
två händer har, men där den första inte vet vad den andra gör. slut i kras och hjälp det sänder, när det står där med sina tomma händer. —————————————————————-
sverigedemokraterna:
och så ännu ett smutsigt år, står där på tå, i väntan på att bli rentvådd.
——————————————————————

text:
지난 11월 27일, 성남동 나비문고에서 <코끼리 가면>을 쓰신 노유다 작가님과 이를 펴내신 나낮잠님과 함께 <코끼리 가면 북토크>가 진행되었습니다:) <코끼리 가면>은 성폭력 생존자인 ‘나’의 복수에 관한 글그림책이자 목소리 소설(novels of voices)입니다. 가족 내 성폭력, 아동 성폭력 피해 생존자인 작가가 10년동안 이야기를 다듬어 세상에 전하는 메세지를 담고 있습니다. 직접 그린 삽화와 가족사진을 더해 어린 날의 아픔을 더 생생하게 재현해 내고 있는데요,  이 책의 '나'는 가해자인 두 오빠를 두둔하기 위해 생을 위협하는 친모, 침묵을 강요하는 친부, 성폭력 피해 후유증에 의한 양극성 장애와 맞서 싸우며 작품을 완성합니다. 첫 번째 문학 공감 스토리텔링 공모전에서 우수상을 수상해 그 작품성을 인정받기도 했습니다. 
만남의 자리에서는 각자 자기가 가졌던 크고 작은 상처들을 나누고 위로하는 시간부터 시작해서 현 사회가 얼마나 폭력으로부터 취약한지 대화를 나누기도 했습니다. 그 외에도 아주 다양한 이야기가 오갔답니다:) 서로를 치유하고 위로하는. 또 응원이 될 수도 있는 자리였습니다, 추운 겨울 저녁, 다양한 입장에 선 우리가 한자리에 모여 <코끼리 가면>을 주 축으로 서로의 의견과 기억을 나눌 수 있었던 아주 빛나는 시간이었습니다. 
참석해주신 모든 분께 감사를 전합니다

name: 울산대 페미니즘 모임 FACE
tweet_full:
지난 11월 27일, 성남동 나비문고에서 <코끼리 가면>을 쓰신 노유다 작가님과 이를 펴내신 나낮잠님과 함께 <코끼리 가면 북토크>가 진행되었습니다:) <코끼리 가면>은 성폭력 생존자인 ‘나’의 복수에 관한 글그림책이자 목소리 소설(novels of voices)입니다. 가족 내 성폭력, 아동 성폭력 피해 생존자인 작가가 10년동안 이야기를 다듬어 세상에 전하는 메세지를 담고 있습니다. 직접 그린 삽화와 가족사진을 더해 어린 날의 아픔을 더 생생하게 재현해 내고 있는데요,  이 책의 '나'는 가해자인 두 오빠를 두둔하기 위해 생을 위협하는 친모, 침묵을 강요하는 친부, 성폭력 피해 후유증에 의한 양극성 장애와 맞서 싸우며 작품을 완성합니다. 첫 번째 문학 공감 스토리텔링 공모전에서 우수상을 수상해 그 작품성을 인정받기도 했습니다. 
만남의 자리에서는 각자 자기가 가졌던 크고 작은 상처들을 나누고 위로하는 시간부터 시작해서 현 사회가 얼마나 폭력으로부터 취약한지 대화를 나누기도 했습니다. 그 외에도 아주 다양한 이야기가 오갔답니다:) 서로를 치유하고 위로하는. 또 응원이 될 수도 있는 자리였습니다, 추운 겨울 저녁, 다양한 입장에 선 우리가 한자리에 모여 <코끼리 가면>을 주 축으로 서로의 의견과 기억을 나눌 수 있었던 아주 빛나는 시간이었습니다. 
참석해주신 모든 분께 감사를 전합니다

in 2006, civil rights activist tarana burke sat in her room, took out a piece of paper, wrote “me too” across the top, and created an action plan for a movement that supported all survivors of sexual violence. now, #metoo has become a global movement, and while its mission is often misinterpreted, tarana is determined to keep working to dismantle the building blocks of sexual violence: power and privilege. “power and privilege doesn't always have to destroy and take -- it can be used to serve and build,” she says. to watch her ted talk from #tedwomen, visit go.ted.com/taranaburke

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

just hours after his depaure from the trump administration became public, breitba, whose traffic and adveising have fallen significan notly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitba editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitba gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitba told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robe mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg repoed.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significan notly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
our woman of the week is actually a group of beautiful and empowering women.
•
this week the hollywood reporter spoke with 6 hollywood leading ladies at the hr round table: glenn close, lady gaga, kathryn hahn, nicole kidman, regina king and rachel weisz. they opened up about how hollywood is different now and one "very subtle" #metoo moment, declaring "ask me anything and i'll answer."
•
the round table covered issues of being a woman in hollywood. this prevalent topic is something we aim to discuss in our april 2019 event ‘lmf women in film festival’ 🎥❤️ •

text: "insecurities".... ever feel like we are on a pedistal and in the spotlight for the world to judge us?  well...we are. and we are sending the messages in which we are judged. 🌎  our posture, our energy,  is what we can control.  don't try to hide your physical flaws, it sends the #wrong message.... it  paints a #picture to the world a #message of insecurity. .. 😦 the only type of attention you'll get is from those who think you are weak or broken. (negative energy)  don't send that message. you are not weak just because your body has flaws....😦 of course it has #flaws ... your body has been with you from the beginning!  it's the only secure thing we have. 😉 . be proud that it has gotten you this far. be in awe that it keeps you alive through all the beatings of #life.  stand with your head held high, and tell a #different #story to the #world.  attract #positive #energy  your body may have flaws but your #conscience #mind is separate from your body. you apart from your body are #flawless .  your #body is a #fortress for your #soul to #exist. 💜💜💜💜💜💜💜💜💜💜#stayoutofyourwheelselfies #selfportrait #selfexpression #selflove #selflovemovement #metoo  #artistsofinstagram #stayoutofyourwheeldeepthoughtsandshit  #selflovemovement

please circulate this as much as you can, so that justice can be served to neelanjana. all of us love her and stand by her side and refuse to be silenced by patriarchy and the violence that it perpetrates.

in part four of this seven part series, we ask no nation for women author @priyankadubeypictures to:

tell us about your childhood experiences... a book that is both shocking and pertinent... in no nation for women, priyanka dubey travels through large swathes of india, over a period of six years, to uncover the accounts of disenfranchised women who are caught in the grip of patriarchy. 
equally, she asks if after the globally-reported december 2012 gang-rape of nirbhaya in new delhi, india’s gender narrative has shifted—and if it hasn’t, what needs to be done to make this a nation worthy of its girls.

text:
o presidente eleito, jair bolsonaro, concorre ao título de personalidade do ano pela revista norte-americana time. 
a competição é realizada desde 1927 e identifica a pessoa ou grupo de pessoas que, para melhor ou pior, tiveram maior influência nos eventos do ano.

a votação está no site da revista e coloca bolsonaro na disputa com outros 54 nomes. entre os concorrentes do militar da reserva estão: as cantoras lady gaga, beyoncé, taylor swift; os presidentes donald trump (eua), emmanuel macron (frança), vladimir putin (rússia) e kim jong-un (coreia do norte); e o empresário jeff bezos (ceo da amazon). em 2017, a personalidade do ano escolhida pela time foi o grupo silence breakers, movimento das mulheres que denunciaram o assédio sexual, conhecido como #metoo. no ano anterior, foi eleito o presidente norte-americano donald trump.

a revista também já estampou em sua capa escolhas polêmicas, como o ditador adolf hitler em 1938 e do aiatolá ruhollah khomeini em 1979.

apesar da enquete ser aberta ao público, a escolha da capa fica a cargo dos editores da revista. a personalidade do ano será revelada em dezembro.

fonte: poder360

text:
https://youtu.be/3brsbtdvunk

https://www.facebook.com/754583111398048/posts/983049658551391/

so i had the absolute pleasure of being involved in the making of this very important ad campaign
everybody’s business 
highlighting woman’s gender based issues in the workplace 
please watch , like and share 😘

https://youtu.be/3brsbtdvunk

fantastic people to work along side and more importantly a very important issue that needs to be shared . 
issues like this shouldn’t be diminished or joked about , these issues are very real and need to be highlighted 
please like and share the campaign for the next 24 hours for our chance to picked as a finalist 😘 - - halfway! 💪🏻 - - 
day 8/film 8
16 days 16 films - - - everybody's business, directed by miranda stern - - -
our eigth finalist of the 16 selected ✨

told through a fictional protagonist's vlog, this film explores gender-based violence in the workplace - something which 1 in 3 women experience, but only 22% of whom ever report. 'if we want things to change then this really has to become ‘everybody’s business’.' the end of the film poses a very direct challenge: transformation must include men if change is going to happen.

will be live at midnight tonight over on:

modernfilms.com/16days16films

available to watch only for sunday 2nd december, the eigth day of 16 days of activism 💪🏻 - - -

special thanks to uk says no more, national film and television school, film4, monroe creative studio, hestia charity and all the filmmakers who entered our 16 films competition.

#whaticando #16days16films - - - [clips from everybody's business (c) miranda stern]

#femalefilmmaker #womeninfilm #metoo #vlog #timesup #uksaysnomore #whaticando #16days16films

text:
2 december, andra raden i andra kapitlet av mio min mio: "det som jag hade varit med om liknar ingenting som någon annan har varit med om.“ nu tror jag det är svårt att va med om mios grej att bli uppsvept av en stor vit varelse och plötsligt vara en kunglighet med sin far.

men jag tar citatet vidare ifrån lindgrens kontext idag. 
väldigt ofta tänker vi människor att ingen annan varit i samma sorts skor. vi är onödigt ensamma i samhället tycks det som. att bära alla saker själv gör dig väldigt trött.

jag tänker på #metoo rörelsen som get många personer perspektiv på sin upplevda ensamhet. 
jag tänker på #aldrigensam och alla människor som känt sig instängda i stigmatiserande diagnoser och psykisk ohälsa. jag tänker på människor som verkar inom #suicidezero

jag tänker på hur viktiga mellanmänskliga möten, se varandra i ögonen och om vi inte varit med om samma sak så har vi ändå öron att lyssna med och en vilja att förstå. jag tror det är vår lott att söka varandra.

#associationsleken #reutersreflektionsluckor

@arimelber ❤ @katyturnbc 💪😘👍 i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still, today, right now.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

my second standing sketching. it took much more time than drawing while sitting, and made my right arm tired, but i needed to maintain this angle so i had no choice. the security uncle saw me standing for too long (almost 1 hour) he got worried and asked me to sit on a platform nearby, but if course i couldn't.
mortuary bath is the first structure after the gate of golconda fort, hyderabad, india. it was used for the ceremonial bathing of the dead body of the royal family.
the fort was huge and so beautiful i wanted to stop and sketch at every corner. a swiss girl i met there suggested i should work there so i could draw it anytime.

text:
im 7 years old, standing in the waves. 8, 9, 10 foot waves. they keep rolling in. each one, bigger, stronger, meaner than the one before. 
trying to keep my balance. 
they keep hitting me, over, and over, and over again. it's so cold! i can't see the sun. it's dark. im so alone!

finally i get knocked down. but i get back up. then get knocked down. then up again. then down again. im shivering, not just from the cold water, but from the pain. 
each time being cut, and bruised by the coral, and rocks. i'm trying to stand up, i'm trying to hold my breath!

im bleeding, i'm bruised. it's hurts. but i keep getting up. 
each wave, i just stay there. they get bigger, and bigger. they just don't stop. years go on. 
i'm not a young girl anymore. 
but the waves keep coming. 
i learn how to jump over the waves. dive into them. 
then one day, they stop! the storm is gone. 
the ocean is calm. just a ripple here and there. birds chirping. the water turns warm. the sun is shining. not a cloud in the sky. 
it's unsettling, but calm. 
the cuts have turned into scars. the bruises are gone. 
but i still feel the pain. it's hurts inside of me now. the pain is deep. 
what do i do now. all i've known is pain. 
i need to leave this beach. i need to turn around and walk away from here. 
why have i stayed here so long?! i can turn around and walk away. 
that's what i'll do. no looking back. 
the storm is gone. -crg

#poem #myheart #truth #love #life #poetry #heal #story #metoo #abuse #rape #recover #my #art #forgive

text:
this is me
yesterday
trying
💛
yesterday i went to a wonderful celebration, a 5 year anniversary shindig for two inspirational women. they're teachers and do some exciting things in there feild. much in awe. i got to hang out with one of my all time best friends (and family💛 ) one who i'm proud of, but also i'm proud of us, hit the bottom with someone and the climb back up is breathtaking and heartwarming. 🍰🎉
however.
i did a scary thing before i went to the party. lunch with an important person. it went well. 🎟️🚄🚇
i got myself round london on my own. i didn't totally suck at solo adulting. i definitely wasn't fully connected, i tried to remain present, but it's not my natural go to. i felt like there should have been more feels. i'm sure i'll get them in a few days. it often takes me a few sleeps to process bigger things and feelings. 📸
id- katherine giving a thumbs up with a cheesy grin, hair down, orange dinoboy tattoo visible, wearing her favourite price of vulva jewellery, the flying fanny flaps.

text:
蕩婦遊行 2018

就在去年的蕩婦遊行後的大約兩個星期，香港也發生了me too事件。一位女運動員在臉書上訴說了自己14歲的時候被前教練侵犯一事。此事細節與對錯並非我今日想講的重點，只是想針對在事情發酵期間，從那些攻擊事主的言論中透露出的幾個社會問題。我們的主題是蕩婦遊行，因為社會對性侵受害者有一個理想中應有的樣子，不應衣著暴露，你穿的少穿得性感就是可以被侵犯的蕩婦。那時候我看了該運動員的臉書留言，發現在社會的眼裡不是只有穿得少的女人才是蕩婦，不懂得潔身自愛和異性保持距離還願意上對方家的就是蕩婦；只要“不即時反抗”的受害者就是蕩婦；受害者事後還跟施暴者來往的就是蕩婦；只要受害者不報警就是自願的蕩婦；不即時報警拖了很久才報的就是明明自願卻反口誣告的蕩婦；我們都可以想像法院宣判被告無罪後受害者更加會被鞭笞的體無完膚。

根絕以上種種的言論，我們可以整理出來他們認為一個受害者應該有的樣子。首先她必須衣著言行端莊，懂得主動和異性保持距離，而不是“天真”的一個人跑去教練的家。當對方做出不恰當的行為，她必須第一時間表現出強烈的反抗並逃離現場，無論對方是什麼身份地位和她有任何權力地位不對等的關係她都必須切割老死不相往來，並堅強的馬上報警。只要她沒有符合以上任何一點，她就是一個蕩婦。而這以上的種種言論中最讓我驚恐的部分是，這一切竟然是社會對一個未成年的14歲女孩的要求。就算我們的法律明文規定，任何涉及16歲以下未成年少男少女的性行為都是違法的，哪怕受害者同意也不能算數，大家依然可以理所當然的無視這條法律的意義在於保護成熟度不足的兒童，然後理直氣壯的要求一個未成年的兒童必須深知如何不成為一名蕩婦。我們的社會對女性的要求苛刻到，連小孩都不放過。

就這件事我特別想指責媒體為了銷量的不負責任行為。當時改名運動員並無開名加害者姓名，表達講出來只為了鼓勵大家不要繼續啞忍，但香港01自行挖掘並跟踪疑似加害者並將其曝光人前。最後這些帳卻回到改名女運動員身上，被要求為可能令無辜者身敗名裂的責任負責。這件事更明確的讓我們看到社會如何將一切歸咎到受害者身上（“blame the victim”），受害者甚至得為媒體的過錯承擔責任。

一年過去，案件審判結束，女運動員的臉書因抵不住長期的霸凌而關閉，現在由她朋友協助經營的臉書專頁只有幾十個人在follow，每一篇帖文只有單位數的like，但每篇帖文下都依然有人在譴責她，冷嘲熱諷。她完美示範了在這個父權的社會，每位性侵受害者要說出自己的經歷需要付出多大的代價，哪怕像她這麼優秀，在巨大輿論壓力下仍然可以突破個人記錄，為香港贏得自1954年亞運首面田徑個人項目獎牌的運動員。相信經歷過她的事後，香港的氛圍對受害人將更不友善，這是需要我們繼續努力的事。

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitba doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subve elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
beauty has always been associated with sickness, not with health. the most priceless tulip bulbs in the 1637 tulipmania were infected with a virus that rendered the petals variegated and multicolored. most fashion models until recently sported bodies that can charitably be described only as anorectic or emaciated.

but recent developments have plunged the pathologizing of pulchritude into a nadir. today, the very complimenting of beauty has been pathologized and criminalized. women the world over are on a crusade to outlaw beauty and the discourse that it ineluctably engendered for millennia.

nowadays, women protest indignantly when told that they are attractive. incredibly and inanely, they label "abuse" even merely verbal expressions of admiration: they feel that their boundaries are breached and their trust betrayed. women feel objectified and dehumanized, as though their beauty were an alien and irrelevant aspect of their being, somewhat awkward and shameful.

women claim vociferously that to mark their beauty and sex appeal is to ignore their other offerings and to treat them as inferior. can't one make the same argument about any other human trait? should a public intellectual rail against being singled out for her intellect, a mother for her compassion, an athlete for her physique, and an entrepreneur for her vision and daring? all these are innate, mostly inherited properties, cultivated through the years - exactly like beauty and allure.

women are recklessly undermining the very foundations of inter-gender communication, conflating aggression with assertiveness, abrasiveness with boundary setting, and narcissism with self-confidence. we are going to pay a horrible price for this sick dynamic: pathologizing the beautiful dance between men and women, pathologizing beauty itself.

#beauty #health #women #men #metoo #sexual #harassment #sickness #compliment #samvaknin #gender

text:
#چرچیل
از این صداقت #لاهوتی خوشم میاد همه اطرافیان و خانواده درجه اول خودشو تو شهر خودش برد سر کار و بالاترین پست های شهری را به آنها داد اینو میگن یه فامیل ویا پدر و یا دایی و یا عمه جان مرد و یا خاله مرد خوب مخلصانه خدمت میکنه هر اداره ای تو لنگرمد بری یه لاهوتی توش میبینی  متاسفانه فامیل ما هم میشن البته ایشون در مقابل آیت الله لاهوتی اشکوری که داماد پدربزرگ بنده بودن شاگرد هم به حساب نمی آیند . بنده هیچ علاقه ای ندارم که ایشان را از فامیل های بنده بدانید 
وقتی این همه جوان داره میره خدمت لب مرز پسر آقای لاهوتی در دفتر پدر دوران سربازی می گذراند آن یکی اقا کمیل شهردار  چمخاله هستند یکی دیگه شن و ماسه های  شرق گیلان میبلعد البته منصف هستند مرز بندی کردن قسمتی برای جناب جعفرزاده می باشد . اینقدر هم دلسوز هستند ایشون پروژه ساخت تلکابین لنگرود را به پسرشون دادند البته به خاطر اینکه زودتر تموم بشه اگر فکر دیگر کنی مدیونی.
به بهانه پروژه تلکابین تمام زمین های اون مسیر خریدن البته برای کار خیر. آقا فرهاد لاهوتی هم پسر دیگر ایشان به پست سخت و طاقت فرسای مشاور فرماندار مشغول به کار هستند .

از این صداقت  خوشم میاد همه اطرافیان و خانواده درجه اول خودشو تو شهر خودش برد سر کار و بالاترین پست های شهری را به آنها داد اینو میگن یه فامیل ویا پدر و یا دایی و یا عمه جان مرد و یا خاله مرد خوب مخلصانه خدمت میکنه هر اداره ای تو لنگرمد بری یه لاهوتی توش میبینی  متاسفانه فامیل ما هم میشن البته ایشون در مقابل آیت الله لاهوتی اشکوری که داماد پدربزرگ بنده بودن شاگرد هم به حساب نمی آیند . بنده هیچ علاقه ای ندارم که ایشان را از فامیل های بنده بدانید 
وقتی این همه جوان داره میره خدمت لب مرز پسر آقای لاهوتی در دفتر پدر دوران سربازی می گذراند آن یکی اقا کمیل شهردار  چمخاله هستند یکی دیگه شن و ماسه های  شرق گیلان میبلعد البته منصف هستند مرز بندی کردن قسمتی برای جناب جعفرزاده می باشد . اینقدر هم دلسوز هستند ایشون پروژه ساخت تلکابین لنگرود را به پسرشون دادند البته به خاطر اینکه زودتر تموم بشه اگر فکر دیگر کنی مدیونی.
به بهانه پروژه تلکابین تمام زمین های اون مسیر خریدن البته برای کار خیر. آقا فرهاد لاهوتی هم پسر دیگر ایشان به پست سخت و طاقت فرسای مشاور فرماندار مشغول به کار هستند .

text:
since last week you might have seen pictures and videos from the 'let's talk about yest' demonstration in copenhagen. in aarhus (and odense and aalborg) there were demos for consent-based rape legislation too. the copenhageners and the so called national press don't care to mention us, they think they are bigger and better than the rest of us. i don't blame them, due to the national media rarely getting their asses out of the capital, they don't know a thing about what's happening outside their  own bubble.
these are pictures from aarhus. the event was large, noicy and powerful. so many voices of survivors and supporters coming together! thinking about it makes me so proud and so humbled to have been part of giving voice to these people. for a moment we were one, and it was strong, beautiful and empowering.

#letstalkaboutyes #ibelieveher #believeher #metoo #consentculture #consent #justconsent #samtykkebaseretlovgivningnu #mitaarhus #herstoryourstory #samtykkeersexet #samtykkelov #ikkeenmere

@everydaysexismprojectdanmark @amnestydanmark @miklpisofficial @jasminidriss

p. s. credits to the local press for being there @tv2ostjylland ❤️ #notallpress

text:
when women come together, magic happens.. .
.
i was surely in my element and fortunate to be in the company of africa's most inspiring and powerful women at the @motsepefoundation sdg5 breakfast. some, i'm fortunate enough to have as my mentors. .
we were inspired by keynotes, panel discussions and the presence of thought leaders such as un deputy secretary general, amina mohammed, graca machel, thuli madonsela, and our amazing wef family,  rapelang rabana, naadiya moosajie among others.
.
.
thank you dr precious motsepe and the motsepe foundation for hosting this beautiful event. i look forward to working together to accelerate progress on sdg5 by 2030 and onwards. .
.
"freedom cannot be achieved unless women have been emancipated from all forms of oppression". (nelson mandela)

tarana burke, a social activist and community organizer, began using the phrase "me too" in 2006, on the myspace social network[18] as part of a campaign to promote "empowerment through empathy" among women of color who have experienced sexual abuse, particularly within underprivileged communities.[10][19][20] burke, who is creating a documentary titled me too, has said she was inspired to use the phrase after being unable to respond to a 13-year-old girl who confided to her that she had been sexually assaulted. burke later wished she had simply told the girl, "me too".[18]
*******************************

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

mistä tänä vuonna puhuttiin? mitkä aiheet ja uutiset mullistivat maailmaa, ajatteluamme ja toimintaamme? 
ilmastonmuutos, muovin määrä meressä, teknologian piilovalta, sodat ja me too -liike. siinä hs:n toimituksen valitsemat vuoden 2018 merkittävimmät uutisaiheet. 
koska uutiset usein kertovat rumia totuuksia maailmasta, hs suunnitteli rumat jouluvillapaidat ilmentämään vuoden tärkeimpiä aiheita. 
hs vie joulupaitoja aihepiirien asiantuntijoille ja vaikuttajille, kuten martti ahtisaarelle ja elina knihtilälle,  ja kysyy heiltä ratkaisuja, joilla rumista totuuksista tulee vähän kauniimpia. miten maailma muuttuu paremmaksi?

text:
в наличии 
мячик с петельками - это большое количество всевозможных цветных петелек и разнофактурных тканей + погремушка.

разработан специально для развития мелкой моторики и тактильных ощущений детей до года.

перебирая петельки, малыш понимает, что они гладкие или шершавые, пробует “на вкус”, и, тем самым познаёт мир.
яркий мячик стимулирует ребенка хватать и держать его маленькими пальчиками. 
мягкий и приятный на ощупь мячик, издает звук зёрнышек, стимулирующий органы слуха малыша. 
мячик поможет малышу развить в себе новые навыки, побуждая его к активным действиям!

мякиши идеально подходят для самых маленьких, поскольку у них нет острых углов. 
удачно подобранный размер, цвет, звук, яркие и понятные рисунки развивают мышление, координацию движений и совершенствуют моторику нежных детских пальчиков.

изготовлено из гипоаллергенных материалов.

text:
in part four of this seven part series, we ask no nation for women author @priyankadubeypictures to:

tell us about your childhood experiences... a book that is both shocking and pertinent... in no nation for women, priyanka dubey travels through large swathes of india, over a period of six years, to uncover the accounts of disenfranchised women who are caught in the grip of patriarchy. 
equally, she asks if after the globally-reported december 2012 gang-rape of nirbhaya in new delhi, india’s gender narrative has shifted—and if it hasn’t, what needs to be done to make this a nation worthy of its girls.

check out the link in our bio

text:
明日は年末恒例の「流行語大賞」の発表である。
すでにノミネート作30語が選ばれているので、一応紹介しておこう。
♣️
あおり運転
悪質タックル
eスポーツ
（大迫）半端ないって
おっさんずラブ
gafa（ガーファ）
仮想通貨／ダークウェブ
金足農旋風
カメ止め
君たちはどう生きるか
筋肉は裏切らない
グレイヘア
計画運休
高プロ（高度プロフェッショナル制度）
ご飯論法

tiktok
なおみ節
奈良判定
ひょっこりはん
ブラックアウト
ボーっと生きてんじゃねえよ！
＃metoo
もぐもぐタイム
♠️
例によって、聞いたことない言葉が多数含まれるが、#ストップ御朱印転売、入ってないかあ。結構、いい線いっていたと思うんだが。少なくとも、御朱印関連は1つくらいねえ。
それはそうと、「半端ないって」や「そだねー」「金農」あたりは、大賞になってもいいかなあと思うが、「首相案件」とか「#metoo 」とかのイデオロギー色の強い案件はやめといてほしい。とかいって、そういうのが選ばれがちなのは知っているが。
ちなみにではあるが、私の2018年流行語大賞は「ハズキルーペだーいすき」。私の周囲では間違いなく大流行していた。近年稀に見るくらいに。ということで、いよいよ師走です。

text:
ultimo incontro: passata la giornata mondiale contro la violenza sulla donna, per ricordarci che “non è normale che sia normale”, abbiamo presentato per tutta la settimana i video degli incontri di donne (non più) anonime – confronto sul femminicidio, un progetto ideato e diretto da daniela trincia per albumarte. un anno di incontri e di confronti in un dibattito articolato e spesso molto emozionante, per il quale vogliamo ringraziare ancora una volta i protagonisti qui citati: luisa betti dakli, giornalista; francesca guerisoli, critica d’arte; silvia giambrone, artista; clara tosi pamphili, storica e critica della moda e della arti applicate; caterina boccardi, scrittrice/attrice; sara allegrucci – matteo bolognese, attori; maria francesca palermo, avvocatessa penalista; teresa dattilo, psicologa psicoterapeuta; ursula franco, medico criminologo; maria francesca palermo, avvocatessa penalista; giacomo grifoni; avvocato bernetti andrea, psicologo psicoterapeuta; giuseppe esposito; flavia posabella, psicologa psicoterapeuta; rosa jijon, artista; alessandra sannella, sociologa; cristiana guerra, educatrice presso case famiglia per minori; stefania salatino, psicologa psicoterapeuta; teresa margolles, artista; angel moya garcia, curatore e co-direttore artistico della tenuta dello scompiglio; tomaso binga, artista; maura misiti, demografa; titti carrano, presidente associazione d.i.re donne in rete contro la violenza; roxy in the box, artista; tiziana colamonico mensorio, avvocatessa. questa still proviene dal video che racconta la sintesi dell’ultimo incontro con focus: “impegno sociale nei sobborghi dell’anima e delle città”. roma 2 dicembre 2017. per guardare questo e tutti i video di albumarte, seguiteci sul nostro canale youtube ➡ link in bio

text:
"but be clear: .
this is a movement about the one-in-four girls and the one-in-six boys who are sexually assaulted every year and carry those wounds into adulthood. .
it’s about the 84% of trans women who will be sexually assaulted this year and the indigenous women who are three-and-a-half times more likely to be sexually assaulted than any other group. .
or people with disabilities, who are seven times more likely to be sexually abused. .
it’s about the 60 percent of black girls like me who will be experiencing sexual violence before they turn 18, and the thousands and thousands of low-wage workers who are being sexually harassed right now on jobs that they can’t afford to quit."
.
 thank you @taranajaneen. for starting the #metoo movement a decade ago. .
for reminding us all what the movement is about.
.
for seeing the individual and the structure at the same time.
.
thank you for your courage to continue, it allows me to do the same.
.
go to @taranajaneen s bio for the whole ted talk.
#metoo #taranaburke

text:
the fact that you are still here gives you an advantage. my prayer is that we should not look back. let us look straight ahead.

our experiences, our life lessons derived from our mistakes, defeats and setbacks, must act as springboards to make us start over again. 
what we should consider as a fact is that life changes. you may not have the same life as before, but you can still enjoy your life!" let us learn to accept our mistakes, say sorry where necessary and even say thank you to whoever it may concern. 
at the end of the day, we should be able to look back and appreciate the roles we play as individuals based on the teamwork spirit. 
together as one people, we can go forward  click www.paypal.me/destinyinstitute to help those in need and support our activities. $5 can make a difference. in jesus name we pray. amen.

text:
kekerasan seksual di transportasi dan ruang publik masih banyak terjadi. 
menurut catatan tahunan komnas perempuan di tahun 2017, dari 350.000 kasus kekerasan terhadap perempuan yang tercatat, 20% diantaranya terjadi di ruang publik.
.
korban masih saja disalahkan, aparat hukum pun melakukan viktimisasi sementara pelaku bebas berkeliaran. belum adanya aturan khusus tentang kekerasan seksual membuat pencegahan dan penanganan kekerasan seksual terhambat.
.
namun begitu sudah ada ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual yang direncanakan menjadi payung hukum masih belum disahkan hingga kini.
.
yuk kita kumpul bersama untuk mendorong pengesahannya! sampai bertemu di sana!
.
#gerakbersama #16haktp #sahkanruupks #metoo #hearmetoo

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
актуальная проблема в наше время:почему ко мне не приходят подписчики?
я тоже задаюсь этим вопросом,поэтому давай вместе разберёмся.
итак,я расскажу тебе,что делать,что бы твой профиль стал популярным.

1.пиши посты.📌
аудиторию привлекают не только красивые фото,но и хороший текст.про что писать?про актуальный сейчас темы.например:vlog,рассказывай о своей жизни,историях из неё;если хорошо знаешь английский или другой языки,пиши посты о знаменитых фразах языка или учи других говорить на нем.и так далее.главное,выбирай то,что интересно тебе.💕
2.единое оформление профиля
у меня это большая проблема.чаще всего людям нравится красивая страница,в которой все в одинаковом тоне.я хотела начать выкладывать что-то такое,но не могу🙈.ведь зимой должны быть только зимние фото...а иногда хочется вспомнить лето.если твой профиль только появился,попробуй выкладывать фото в едином стиле💕
3.твоя фишка📌
придумай то что отделяет тебя от других людей.об этом ты сможешь рассказать в графе:о себе.лично меня ничего не отличает,но я придумала своему профилю интересное название:кудри,путешествия и мода(можно выделиться и названием).💕
4.бери рекламу📌
наверняка ты подписан на блогера,у которого много подписчиков.у него ты и можешь взять рекламу.реклама бывает недорогая и дорогая,смотря к у какого профиля брать.у профилей с аудиторией 1к-10к стоимость может быть от 70 до 150-200р.(у каждого индивидуально).соответственно чем больше подписчиков-тем больше цена.я советую брать рекламу не самую дешёвую, а 
среднюю по цене.
5.комментируй и лайкай📌
ты можешь на писать комментарий у известного блоггера,его увидит большая аудитория и возможно подпишется.

если соблюдать все эти пункты,у тебя есть возможность стать популярным.пробуй,и главное верь в себя🌟💕#kate_chernykh18♥️##l4like #l4l#followmeto #follow4followback #backfollow #liketime #likeforlikes #likeforfollow #likelike #liker #liked #like4follow #liketolike #likeaboss #likeit#likeforlikealways #follow#followforfollowback #follow4followback#metoo#wow#взаимно #взаимныелайки #взаимнаяподписка  #вз

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian
